title: chicken casserole
directions: Place thin layer of dressing in a 9 x 14-inch casserole dish. Add chicken.
Heat milk, soups and broth in saucepan; pour over chicken.
Cover with remaining dressing.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Should set approximately 10 minutes before serving.

title: three day coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed on box.
Cool.
Split layers.
Mix coconut, sugar and sour cream.
Set aside 3/4 cup of this mixture. Use the rest for filling between layers.
For frosting add the 3/4 cup of mixture to the Cool Whip and frost the entire cake. Cover loosely and place in refrigerator and leave 3 days before cutting.

title: kraut salad
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and bring to a boil, then add remainder of ingredients.
Mix and let sit overnight in refrigerator.

title: most delicious pie
directions: Beat milk and dream whip until stiff.
Set aside.
In another bowl, pour condensed milk.
Gradually beat in lemon juice and vanilla.
Beat until thick.
Fold condensed milk mixture into the dream whip mixture until well blended.
Place mixture in graham cracker crust and top with pie filling.

title: four-layer blueberry pie
directions: Combine margarine, flour and nuts.
Mix well and pack into a 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Let cool.
In a mixing bowl, combine cream cheese and sugar, beating well with electric mixer.
Using the mixer, add in whipped topping.
Spread 1/3 of this mixture over the cooled crust. Spread pie filling over cream cheese mixture.
Spread remaining over blueberries.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: winter beef stew
directions: In a large, heavy pot saute bacon and drain grease.
Add garlic and beef and brown.
Add bouillon, beer, onion, mint, cumin and pepper; bring to a boil, then simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours until meat is done (remove the onion).
Thicken with flour and water.

title: easy fudge
directions: Melt chocolate cremes in microwave.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add powdered sugar.
Spray dish with Pam. Pour into dish.
Cut in squares before gets too cool.

title: cranberry salad
directions: In food processor, blend cheese, mayonnaise and sugar.
Add cranberry sauce, pineapple, pecans and Cool Whip.
(Process.) Fold in marshmallows.
Freeze.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix and press into pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes; cool.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly with rotary beater.
Beat in remaining ingredients.
Pour into pastry lined pan.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes, until knife inserted 1-inch from edge of crust comes out clean.
(Center will still look soft, but will set later.)

title: spamwiches
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Fill hamburger rolls.
Wrap in foil and bake at 250° for 30 minutes.

title: very crisp oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, margarine and eggs.
Add nuts.
Measure and sift together flour and soda.
Add to egg mixture.
Stir in oatmeal and mix well but gently.
Shape into little balls; place on baking sheet.
Flatten with fork.
Bake in 400° oven for 10 minutes or until crisp and brown.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: strip-n-go naked
directions: Mix all together, but not next to Harris Cabin.

title: mom's chicken salad
directions: Boil chicken until completely done. Dice onions, olives and chicken. Mix everything together in large bowl. Add celery to taste. Add mayonnaise to desired consistency. Chill.

title: beef-and-spinach dip
directions: Cook beef and onion in a large skillet, stirring until beef crumbles and is no longer pink; drain. Stir in cream cheese and next 3 ingredients; cook over low heat, stirring often until cream cheese melts. Sprinkle with Parmesan. Serve with tortilla chips. Yield: 4 cups.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown, drain and cool the ground meat.
Chop the onion, pepper and green and black olives.
Tear lettuce into bite-size pieces. Slightly crumble the Doritos.
Mix all the ingredients, except the dressing, thoroughly.
When ready to serve, pour on Catalina dressing and mix again.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix sugar and sweet potatoes together.
Stir in eggs, then rest of ingredients and mix well with beater.
Pour into deep dish crust.
Bake about 50 minutes at 325°.

title: jelly roll
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread dough into a cookie sheet and bake.
While it is still
hot
from the oven, sprinkle with powdered sugar and turn out
on
a
cloth.
Spread jelly evenly and gently roll.
Let the cloth
stay
around the roll until it cools.
Cut and serve.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: wise man's rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water; add sugar, egg, oil, salt, bran and flour.
Beat until well mixed.
Mixture will be soupy.
Put in covered container.
Refrigerate as needed.
Spoon into greased muffin tins and bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Do not let rise before baking.

title: peanut butter blossoms
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Roll dough in small balls and roll in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Take out of oven and place a Hershey's Kiss on top immediately.

title: 13 day pickle
directions: Wash cucumbers, put in salt brine strong enough to float an egg.
Let stand in this for 6 days; drain.

title: chicken breasts with alfredo sauce
directions: Pound breast thin, dip into milk and then breadcrumbs and brown (this should only take a couple of minutes).
In oven or broiler, cook cheese bread.
Heat alfredo sauce.
When breasts are cooked, lay one on each cooked garlic bread, top with alfredo sauce, sprinkle with parmesan cheese.
Place in broiler for just a few minutes until mixture starts to bubble.
Serve with a salad. This is a very easy and quick meal and it is DELICIOUS.

title: chocolate popcorn fudge
directions: Melt chocolate in saucepan.
Add sugar, milk, water, butter or butter substitute and salt.
Boil to soft ball stage (234° to 238°).
Remove from fire.
Add flavoring and popped corn.
Cool to room temperature.
Stir until creamy.
Pour into well buttered, shallow pan.
Cut in squares.

title: easy cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese. Mix with Ranch party dip mix. Roll into ball. Cover with chopped pecans. Roll into ball and serve with your favorite crackers.

title: marinated sweet pepper
directions: Sweat peppers in saute pan until tender.
Toss in bowl with vinegar and basil.
Chill 1 hour before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: asparagus and sour cream
directions: Boil asparagus until tender.
Arrange on platter and pour sour cream over evenly.
Garnish with finely grated egg yolk.

title: crepes
directions: Sift together the dry ingredients into a mixing bowl.
Stir in remaining ingredients and beat until smooth.
Oil an 8-inch iron skillet and heat.
Pour in 1/4-cup of batter and tilt skillet until batter is round.
Let cook until bubbles form.
Then quickly flip crepe over and let it get only lightly tan.
Stack with paper toweling until ready to serve.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar. Add eggs.
Add bananas. Add dry ingredients. Add soda to buttermilk and add to batter.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into tube pan or loaf pans.
(Pans should be greased and floured.)
Bake at 300° for about 1 hour.

title: weight watchers delight dessert
directions: Mix ingredients together throughout and pour into a large baking dish.
Chill in refrigerator until jello is set.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Store in tightly covered container.
Use 1/3 cup mixture in a cup of hot water!

title: low-fat skillet chili
directions: Brown broken up turkey until no pink remains.
Add green pepper, onion, kidney beans and seasoning mix to meat in skillet. Stir in water.

title: squaw corn
directions: Cut bacon into 1-inch pieces.
Cook until almost done.
Drain off grease.
Add onion; cook until onion is soft.
Add corn; season as desired.
Heat and serve.
It's great on mashed potatoes.

title: turtle sauce piquant 1
directions: Prepare a roux as for Turtle Stew 2.
Add onions and pepper. Cook until tender.
Add celery and parsley.
Cook and stir; add garlic.
Add 1 cup cold water and stir.
While this is being done, brown the turtle meat in cooking oil.
Place the meat in a large stew pot and add the roux and remaining ingredients.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer until meat is tender.
Add salt, pepper and cayenne to taste.
Add more water, if necessary, while cooking.
Serve over rice or spaghetti.

title: layered salad
directions: Put in layers as listed.
Sprinkle cheese on last.
Mix sugar and Miracle Whip and spread on top.
Chill overnight.
Sprinkle on Bac*Os and stir 1 hour before serving.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with milk and sour cream, beginning and ending with flour.
Add vanilla and lemon extract.
Pour in tube pan and bake at 300° for 2 hours.
Turn upside down as soon as it comes out of the oven.

title: pork chops and sweet potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain potatoes and place in shallow baking dish.
Top with orange slices, then pork chops.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper, then brown sugar.
Bake covered for 1 hour. Remove cover and bake about 30 minutes more.

title: baked apples with sausage stuffing
directions: Core apples and pare each about 1/4 of the way down. Carefully scoop out center to make hollow shells; reserve scooped out pulp.
In a large skillet cook onion in butter until tender. Add sausage and bacon.
Add reserved apple pulp, brown sugar, sage, thyme, orange peel, salt, pepper and walnuts.
Cover it up for 2 minutes.
Spoon this mixture into apple shells.

title: chinese sunday pork
directions: Drain pineapple, saving 3 tablespoons juice.
Mix juice with 1/2 cup water, soy sauce, cornstarch, vinegar and pepper.
Set aside.
Cut pork into strips and brown pork in hot oil.
Add garlic and ginger.
Cook 1 minute.
Add onion and carrots.
Cook 1 minute.
Stir sauce.
Add to skillet with pineapple and peppers. Cook until sauce thickens.

title: mary ellen's shrimp
directions: Steam peeled shrimp for 3 minutes with carrot, celery, onion and salt.
Put in ice water to chill.
Remove and place in bowl. Add juice of the three lemons, garlic, both oils, red onions (sliced thin), olives, oregano and basil.
Cover and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Stir often.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Mix pulp and egg.
Alternately add milk and dry ingredients. Stir in margarine.
Pour into greased pan 1 inch deep.
Bake at 300° for about 1 hour or until done.

title: pineapple angel
directions: Mix gelatine in boiling water.
Add pineapple, sugar, lemon juice and Dream Whip.
Mix pineapple mixture and pour over cake pieces.
Sprinkle coconut over top.

title: raisin filled cookies
directions: Mix dough and roll out on a floured board.
Cut out with round cookie cutter, make one for the bottom and another for the top (cut a slit in the top one or use a thimble to make a small round hole in the center of the top).
Put filling in the center and seal around the edges.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Set aside.
Mix sugar and butter in a large bowl.
Add egg.
Alternately add flour and yeast mixture. Refrigerate batter in an airtight bowl for several hours or overnight.
It will keep for a week or more.

title: spaghetti
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Add tomatoes, sauce, mushrooms, parsley, oregano, basil, rosemary, garlic, bay leaf and salt; simmer 1 hour.
Cook noodles as directed.

title: nellie's punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water; stir well, then add all other ingredients except ginger ale.
Pour ginger ale in punch bowl just before serving.
Chill punch in refrigerator before serving.
May freeze a small amount of the punch to place in punch bowl to keep punch cool during serving.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Add all ingredients to large mixing bowl.
Lightly mix.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.

title: so-o-o good corn chowder
directions: Cut bacon into small pieces; place in Dutch oven or large skillet and fry.
Remove bacon.
Fry slowly onions and potatoes until golden brown.
Add pepper, salt, milk and corn.
Heat very slowly.
When hot, remove from heat and allow to cool thoroughly. When ready to serve, add bacon pieces and reheat slowly for mealtime.
May add more milk according to degree of thickness preferred for chowder.
Even better if allowed to sit all day and reheat just before mealtime.
Great with green or fruit salad and cornbread.

title: fruit dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients; chill and serve.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix instant pudding according to directions on box.
Add Cool Whip, butter and vanilla flavoring and mix together.
Layer in pan. Start with cookies on bottom to make a good crust, then pour all pudding mixture next.
Sprinkle the rest of the cookies on top of pudding.
Chill for an hour before serving.

title: chinese chicken
directions: Mix ingredients and marinate chicken.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes if bone-in or 30 minutes if boneless.
Baste while baking. Serves 4 to 6.

title: pumpkin pie, no-bake
directions: In a small bowl, blend milk, eggs, cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg and salt. Set aside. In a medium saucepan, sprinkle gelatine over water. Let stand 1 minute. Stir over low heat until dissolved until slightly thickened, about 5 minutes. Blend in milk mixture. Blend in pumpkin. Put in pie crust. Chill until firm. Garnish with whipped topping.

title: spanish onion soup
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Heat crushed garlic in olive oil and toast both sides of bread and save.
Saute onion in olive oil until soft and almost translucent.
Save with bread.
Heat broth (in same pot) until hot.
Add paprika, pepper flakes and another crushed clove of garlic.
Add onion and bread mixture; stir.
Add sherry.
Slowly pour eggs into soup across top.
Cover pot.
Put in oven until egg browns (about 5 minutes).

title: hot dog time barbecued franks
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and celery in butter in a Dutch oven until tender.
Add catsup, water, lemon, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, sugar and mustard.
Cook over low heat 10 minutes; keep stirring.
Add franks.
Simmer 5 minutes until franks are well heated.

title: four layer dip
directions: In a casserole dish, layer (bottom to top layer).
Bottom Layer:
Refried Beans, next, Avocado dip, next, taco seasoning mixture, next, shredded cheese.
Serve with chips.

title: shipwreck casserole
directions: In 9 x 13-inch or 8 x 8-inch greased pan, add 1 layer of thinly sliced onions.
Add layer of thinly sliced potatoes.
Add hamburger on top.
Layer on green beans.
Mix soup with milk and pour over all.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Top with onion rings 10 minutes before done.
Can be prepared and refrigerated the day before.

title: boston brown bread
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, stir together flour, cornmeal, baking powder and soda; stir in buttermilk, molasses, egg white and oil just until blended.
Stir in raisins.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix and pat pretzels, butter and sugar in 9 x 12-inch pan. Bake 8 minutes at 400°.
Cool.
Mix jello and boiling water; stir well.
Add frozen berries; cool until it starts to thicken.
Cream cheese and sugar; fold in Cool Whip and spread over pretzels.
Add strawberry mixture on top and chill until set.

title: best ever unbaked peach pie
directions: Mix milk, lemon juice and Cool Whip by hand.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into 2 pie crusts (either plain or graham cracker).
Top with pecans.
Keep refrigerated until time to serve.
(This pie is so refreshing.)

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain fat.
Prepare broccoli as directed on package.
In blender, mix until smooth the Bisquick, eggs, milk, sage, parsley, salt and pepper.
Grease a casserole dish. Spread beef mixture as first layer, then broccoli as second layer. Spread Bisquick mixture as third layer.
Sprinkle the Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 375° until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 15 minutes before cutting.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Combine ingredients.
Pour batter in dish;
put peaches over batter.
Bake at 300° to 350° until medium brown.

title: kass's potato chip cookies(a delightfully dainty tea cookie)
directions: Cream together the butter and sugar.
Stir in vanilla.
Mix in the potato chips and pecans.
Add the flour and mix thoroughly. Place on lightly greased cookie sheet in rounded balls.
Grease the bottom of a drinking glass and dip into granulated sugar. Then press down each cookie, dipping into sugar between presses. Bake 10 to 15 minutes in 350° oven.
Makes 3 1/2 to 4 dozen cookies.

title: sweet cucumber pickles
directions: Cover whole cucumbers with boiling water (earthenware crock preferable).
Let soak overnight; drain.
Repeat this procedure for three additional nights.
On the fifth day, drain and slice in 1/2-inch pieces.
Combine with next four ingredients; bring to a boil.
Pour over cucumbers and let soak for 2 days.
On the third day, bring to a boil and seal in sterile jars.

title: sopaipillas
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cut in margarine until mixture resembles cornmeal.
Gradually add water, stirring mixture with a fork.
Turn out on a lightly floured surface; knead to a smooth ball.
Divide in half.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Roll each half out in a rectangle about 10 x 12 1/2 x 1/16-inch.
Cut into 2 1/2-inch squares.
Fry 3 or 4 at a time in deep 400° fat for 30 seconds on each side.
Drain.
Roll in sugar and cinnamon if you want it as a dessert.
Or serve hot with honey.

title: mozzarella chicken
directions: Soak chicken in eggs for 2 hours.
Roll crackers into fine crumbs and mix with parsley flakes and garlic salt.
Roll chicken in crumb mixture.
Brown both sides in butter in skillet.
Melt 2 tablespoons of butter in baking dish.
Place chicken in dish. Dissolve chicken bouillon cubes in hot water and pour over chicken. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Last 10 minutes place 1 slice Mozzarella cheese on each breast.
Bake until
melted.

title: scripture 48 cake
directions: Follow mixing directions of any cake mix.
Bake slowly in moderate oven at 350°.

title: hot fudge pudding
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Stir in milk and shortening; mix until smooth.
Fold in nuts and spread in pan.
Sprinkle with 1 cup brown sugar and 4 tablespoons cocoa, mixed.
Pour 1 3/4 cups hot water over the entire batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Invert squares on plates; dip sauce from pan over each.

title: party punch
directions: Put strawberries and Rose wine in punch bowl.
Cover with Saran Wrap for 1 hour.
Stir in remaining ingredients.

title: five cup salad or dessert
directions: Fold ingredients together and chill before serving.

title: chicken and wild rice casserole
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet over medium heat; add onion, celery and water chestnuts.

Saute 10 minutes or until tender. Stir in rice, chicken, 3 cups cheese, and next five ingredients. Spoon mixture into 15 x 10-inch baking dish or a 4-quart casserole. Top with breadcrumbs, if desired.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and bake 5 more minutes. Serves at least 10.

title: double apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Place sliced apples in large bowl. Sprinkle flour over apples and stir until coated.
In saucepan, combine apple juice concentrate, cornstarch, cinnamon and nutmeg. Stir until smooth.
Place over medium heat and stir constantly until thickened.
Pour juice mixture over apples and mix.
Spoon apples into pie crust.
Place second crust on top, seal edges. Cut slits in top to vent.
Bake 10 minutes at 425°, then lower heat to 375° and bake 35 to 40 minutes.

title: 5 bean soup
directions: Mix all the beans together and put in an airtight container. Mix all the seasonings together and put in a container.

title: anti-pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta as directed on box.
Cut cheese, pepperoni and salami into bite size pieces.
Mix all ingredients together.

title: tropical fruit and nut bars
directions: Drain pineapple.
Reserve juice.
Mix gelatine and juice in saucepan.
Let stand one minute.
Stir over low heat until completely dissolved (about 5 minutes).
Stir in honey, pineapple, nuts, raisins and coconut.
Turn into 9-inch square pan.
Chill until firm.
Cut into bars.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat. Add taco seasoning.
Line large pan with chips. Add all other ingredients to browned meat.
Mix well.
Pour over chips. Top
with cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: Saute onions and bell pepper in butter until tender.
Stir in chicken, 1 cup cheese, sour cream, hot sauce and pepper.
Roll each biscuit 1/4-inch thickness and spread with about 2 tablespoons chicken mixture.
Roll up biscuits, jellyroll fashion, pinching edges to seal.
Place rolls in lightly greased 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Combine soup and milk in saucepan; mix well and cook until thoroughly heated.
Pour soup over roll-ups.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake an additional 2 to 3 minutes or until cheese melts.
Yield:
5 servings.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Stir dry ingredients.
Combine eggs and oil and add to dry ingredients.
Fold in berries and nuts.
Grease 2 large loaf pans. Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix broccoli, onion, raisins and bacon.
Blend mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Pour over broccoli mixture.
Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours before serving.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix ingredients in mixer and pour into Pyrex dish.

title: sausage-egg casserole
directions: In 13 x 9-inch buttered pan, place bread (buttered on pan side) as close together as possible.
Add sausage and cheese.

title: pork chops for 4
directions: Salt the chops well on both sides, then put into lightly greased baking dish.
Cover chops with brown sugar.
Add slices of lemon and then onion.
Top with catsup; cover and bake one hour at 350°.
Remove cover and finish baking 30 minutes more.

title: scalloped sweet potatoes
directions: Lightly oil a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Preheat oven to 400°. Lay the slices of sweet potatoes in the baking dish, overlapping where necessary.
In a small bowl, combine milk, salt, molasses, nutmeg, ginger and lemon juice.
Pour over sweet potatoes and cover baking dish with foil.
Bake 1 hour or until lightly browned and all liquid is absorbed.
Makes 6 servings.

title: moist baked ham
directions: Put ham in large roaster, adding 10 cups hot water.
Put in cold oven.
Turn heat to 500° and bake 30 minutes.
Turn oven off for 1 hour.
Turn on again for 30 minutes.
Turn off and leave in oven overnight.
Seal with heavy foil before baking.

title: caramel corn(oven style)
directions: Mix brown sugar, butter, corn syrup and salt over medium heat, stirring constantly.
When it starts to boil around side of dish, boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; add soda.
Stir well. Pour over corn.
Mix well.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: Cook cranberries with just enough water to cover.
Cool and put through sieve.
Drain pineapple and add to cranberries.
Chop apple, peel orange and remove slices from skin and chop.
Add to cranberries.
Add sugar and mix well.
Refrigerate.
Can be frozen until used.

title: cranberry orange sauce
directions: Grind cranberries and orange rind together.
Mix jello with 1 cup hot water; add orange juice and sugar.
Combine with the cranberry-orange rind.
Let set until firm.

title: easy pie crust(for quiche or pie)
directions: Mix and shape with hands.

title: red and white taffy twist
directions: Mix in a saucepan all ingredients.
Boil and stir until a drop of the mixture forms a hard ball in cold water.
Stir in 2 teaspoons of vanilla.
Divide the mixture in half and stir in red food coloring in one half.
When the mixture cools enough to handle, pull it until it's satiny and stiff.
Pull into long strips, 1/2-inch wide.
Twist red and white stripes together. Cut with buttered scissors into 1-inch pieces.

title: double chocolate sugar cookies
directions: Melt 1 cup chocolate.
Beat butter until fluffy.
Gradually add 1 cup of sugar.
Add egg, milk and vanilla.
Add melted morsels.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix oleo, cream cheese, milk and garlic.
Heat in a pan on low heat until creamy.
Mix cream-style and whole kernel corn with cheese mixture.
Add green chilies.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Bake at 350° about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sweet and sour green beans
directions: Cook bacon in skillet and set aside.
Saute chopped onion in bacon grease.
While this is cooking, combine vinegar and sugar; bring to a boil.
Mix onions with beans and pour into casserole. Pour vinegar and sugar over top of beans.
Bake, covered, for 30 to 45 minutes at 375°.
Crumble bacon and sprinkle over top when through.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup lukewarm water.
Add the buttermilk and rest of ingredients; mix and cover.
Put in refrigerator in a Tupperware bowl with a tight lid.
Store until ready to use, then pinch off what you need.
Make into biscuits.
No need to let rise; they will rise in the oven.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Cook sugar, margarine and syrup for 2 minutes after boiling starts.
Remove from heat.
Add soda and salt.
Stir until it foams.
Pour slowly over corn and stir gently until corn is covered.
Spread on cookie sheets and bake at 200° for 1 hour. Stir gently twice while in oven.
This takes about 3 cookie sheets.

title: roasted onions
directions: Remove onion skins and trim ends.
Cut onions in half from stem to root end.
In medium bowl, stir together olive oil, garlic, salt, pepper and mint.
With hands, coat onions with the mixture and place in roaster or shallow dish.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Baste with dish juices and continue roasting for another 15 minutes or until onions are soft when pierced.
Remove from oven; drizzle generously with balsamic vinegar.
Arrange on platter.
Serves 4.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Stir dry ingredients; cut in shortening until mixture is as fine as meal. Add milk, making a soft dough. Knead lightly on floured board. Roll to 1/2 inch thickness and cut. Bake in hot oven (450°) for 12 minutes.

title: easy coconut custard pie
directions: Mix all ingredients; blend well.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350° or until crust is brown and custard is firm.
(Mine took longer, 60 minutes.)

title: baked squash
directions: Slice, boil, drain and mash squash.
Saute onion in butter. Add cream and crushed crackers, then squash.
Grease casserole; put in mixture.
Dot with butter and bread crumbs.
Bake for 30 minutes at 400°.

title: aunt louise's deviled crab
directions: Mix all ingredients together well and place in individual crab shells or in a casserole.
Dot with butter and bake 20 to 30 minutes at 325°.

title: beef flavored kielbasa(yield: 5 servings)
directions: 1. Preheat oven to 350°.

title: fried vegetable rings
directions: Prepare vegetables; place in large bowl of ice water until cold.
Remove and let dry on paper towels.
Mix batter ingredients and dip assorted vegetables in batter.
Place in deep fryer and fry at 360° until brown.
Drain and salt lightly.
Serve as vegetable side dish or as an appetizer with Ranch type dressing as a dip.

title: ranch style beans
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in butter. Mix together and simmer 18 minutes. Mix all ingredients together and bake, covered, at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: no fuss potato soup
directions: Combine first four ingredients in a large soup pan. Bring to a boil. cover and reduce heat. Simmer for 30 minutes. Stir in soup and milk. Yield: 8 servings.

title: sausage cheese cloud
directions: Place 6 slices of buttered bread in buttered dish, then place 1/2 of cheese and meat over bread.
Then add 6 slices buttered bread, then rest of cheese and meat.
Beat eggs; add milk, onion and seasoning.
Pour this over layered bread and meat.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spiced pineapple
directions: Drain and reserve pineapple.
Measure 1 cup syrup into large saucepan.
Add sugar, vinegar, cloves, allspice and cinnamon. Bring to boiling; reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Add pineapple and cook 3 to 5 minutes or until fruit is heated thoroughly.
Remove from heat.
Serve hot.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Beat egg white and water until frothy with wire beater.
Add nuts and mix.
Add sugar, salt and cinnamon; mix well.
Cover cookie sheet with aluminum foil and butter it.
Spread nuts on sheet.
Bake for 1 hour at 225°.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: vallicelli's chicken cacciatore
directions: Cut breasts into serving size portions.
Dredge in flour and brown in oil on both sides.
Drain any left over oil from pan. Pour pasta sauce over chicken pieces and add 1/2 cup water.
Add green pepper strips.
Simmer, covered, for 30 minutes. Serve with any type of hot pasta noodles.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake until brown 8 to 10 minutes, at 375°.

title: date roll candy
directions: Combine sugar, salt and milk; add butter.
Boil until sugar is dissolved.
Add dates and cook, stirring constantly, for soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and cool to room temperature.
Beat until creamy and thick.
Add nuts and mix thoroughly.
Knead until smooth.
Shape into a roll and chill until firm.
Cut into slices to serve.

title: country corn bread stuffing
directions: Place 4-quart saucepan over medium heat.
Cook bacon until crisp; crumble and set aside.
Use bacon drippings in saucepan; add celery and onion.
Cook until tender.
Add stuffing mix and toss lightly.
Add bacon.

title: taco dip
directions: Place large loaf of cream cheese in dish.
Pour barbecue sauce over it.
Place your favorite crackers and a knife beside the cheese and let people spread the mixture over the crackers.

title: beef taco skillet
directions: Cook beef in skillet until browned. Pour off fat. Add soup, salsa, water, tortillas and 1/2 cup of cheese. Heat to a boil. Cover and cook over low heat 5 minutes or until hot. Top with remaining cheese. Serves 4.

title: quick onion soup
directions: Melt butter
or
margarine
in	saucepan.
Saute sliced onions over medium
heat until golden brown.
Lightly salt and pepper onion slices.
Add	consomme and water and simmer until heated through.
Pour soup into serving bowls.
Place a square of toast in each bowl and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour over chicken.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve over rice.

title: spinach potatoes au gratin
directions: In a 2-quart microwave-safe dish, combine potatoes and water. Cover and microwave on High 8 to 9 minutes or until potatoes are tender, stirring twice.
Drain; set potatoes aside.
In a large microwave-safe bowl, heat butter on High until melted, about 30 seconds.
Add onion.
Microwave, uncovered for 1 to 2 minutes or until tender, stirring once.
Whisk in flour until blended. Gradually stir in milk.
Cook uncovered on High for 2 1/2 minutes; stir and cook 3 to 4 minutes longer, stirring every minute or until sauce is thickened and bubbly.
Stir in cheese and salt. Pour over potatoes.
Add spinach and pimentos; mix well. Microwave, uncovered, on High for 2 to 3 minutes or until heated through, stirring once.
Sprinkle with bacon.
Yields 8 servings.

title: sherried sweet potatoes casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling salted water until just tender. Drain, peel and cut lengthwise into 1/2-inch slices.
Arrange in 13 x 8-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with a little salt.
In saucepan, combine brown sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Blend in orange peel, juice and raisins.
Cook over medium heat until thickened and bubbly (stir often).
Add butter, sherry and walnuts, stirring until butter is melted.
Pour over potatoes. Bake in 325° oven for 30 minutes, or until potatoes are well glazed.
Serves 8.

title: noel nibblers
directions: Combine ground beef, onion and salt.
Mix lightly.
Shape in 1-inch balls.
Brown in skillet. Drain.
Add frankfurters and combine preserves and barbecue sauce.
Simmer 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add pineapple and heat thoroughly.
Makes 10 dozen appetizers.

title: tommy's favorite salad
directions: Mix all together and chill until ready to serve.

title: beef casserole
directions: Brown meat, onions, celery and green peppers.
Mix with soups and add bean sprouts, water chestnuts, 1 tablespoon Worcestershire sauce and soy sauce.
Put in casserole.
Cook at 350° until bubbly, about 35 to 40 minutes.
Put Chinese noodles on top and bake 5 minutes more.

title: ruby allen chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, salt and eggs, then flour and milk in saucepan.
Stir until it begins to thicken.
Pour in baked pie shell and let cool and beat 2 or more egg whites with 2 teaspoons sugar to each egg white until stiff.
Spread on top and brown. May add 1 teaspoon vanilla if desired.

title: cheese stuffed mushrooms(appetizer)
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms.
Finely chop stems.
Cook and stir mushroom stems, green onions and garlic in margarine over medium heat until tender (about 5 minutes).
Remove from heat. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Fill mushroom caps with stuffing mixture.
Place mushrooms, filled side up, in greased baking dish. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 15 minutes.
Yields about 24 appetizers.

title: five layer delight
directions: Mix and press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake
at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Scrub pickles well; rinse and slice.
Slice onions and peppers in thin rounds.
Place in crock or enamel container with cucumbers.
Mix in salt and ice.
Cover with a weighted plate and let stand 3 hours.
Drain.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Prepare stuffing as directed on box.
Prepare soup.
Cook broccoli as directed.
In a large casserole dish, add stuffing, broccoli, chicken soup and cheese (1 cup).
Stir together and add 1/2 cup cheese to top.
Microwave on High for 8 minutes.
Let set 5 minutes and serve.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients together and drop by spoonful into hot fat.
Brown on both sides (3-4 minutes total).
Drain on paper towel.

title: easy gingerbread
directions: Mix flour and spices together.
Cream shortening and sugar together.
Beat eggs and molasses into mixture.
Mix well.
Pour batter into greased 9 inch baking pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: broccoli-pea casserole
directions: Cook rice.
Cook broccoli and drain.
In a 2 quart casserole dish, arrange 1/2 broccoli, 1/2 peas, and 1/2 rice.
Mix mushroom soup, mayonnaise, salt, pepper, cheese, onion, and eggs to make sauce.
Pour 1/2 sauce over dish.
Layer remaining broccoli, peas, and rice and pour remaining sauce over dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Shortly before it finishes cooking, cover with crumbs and brown.

title: hot nacho cheese dip
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage.
Add the rest of ingredients. Soften Velveeta in microwave first.
Keep warm in crock-pot. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix in usual way.
Cook in 350° oven until done.

title: husband's hash supper
directions: Ask wife if she'd mind frying you a skillet of potatoes.
As soon as potatoes have started frying, pull leftover roast from Sunday dinner out of refrigerator.
Ask wife, "How about cutting up some roast and throwing it in?"
Wife will gladly comply. Comment that some sliced onion sure sounds good.
Wife will add sliced onion and cook until tender.
Husband should be setting out plates, silverware, bread and butter during all this conversation. Serve with Ranch Style beans.
Ask wife to please bring ketchup. Tell the kids, "Supper's ready," and eat.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix Crisco, sugars and eggs; beat until creamy.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and water.
Sift flour, soda, baking powder and salt; add to first mixture.
Fold in peanuts. Form into small balls and press with fork dipped in flour.
Bake approximately 8 to 10 minutes or until brown.

title: stacy's favorite crabbies
directions: Mix ingredients.
Spread on muffin halves.
Freeze for 1/2 hour or so, then cut into 4 or 6 wedges, like pizza.
Store in freezer in plastic bags.
To serve, take out as many as you want; bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until hot and slightly browned.

title: stuffed ham slices
directions: Split bread.
Hollow out each half with fork, leaving a 1/2-inch shell. Spread mayonnaise over hollows. Sprinkle with parsley.
Blend cream cheese, celery, cheese, onion and salt. Spoon into bread halves, packing down well and leaving a small hollow down center.
Quarter pickle lengthwise. Roll inside a double thick slice of ham.
Place rolls end to end in center of bottom loaf. Close bread.
Wrap loaf lightly in transparent wrap. Chill several hours.
Makes 16 sandwiches.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients, cover and let stand for 20 minutes.
Add vanilla, eggs, sugar, soda, salt and flour.
Mix well (you do not need a beater).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
While cake is still warm, cover with remaining ingredients (margarine, cream, sugar, vanilla and coconut) that you have heated and cooked a little while.
Put under broiler until coconut is lightly browned.

title: seasoned burgers
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients and mix well.
Shape into 4 patties and place on grill over medium heat for 4 to 5 minutes on each side.
Serve on buns with lettuce and cheese.

title: homemade enchiladas
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown ground beef in skillet; drain.
Add 1 quart water.
Cut up both onions.
Add 1 chopped
onion to beef; add spices.
Cook for 1 hour.
Add can tomatoes; simmer for another hour.
Add 1/4 cup water to cornstarch; mix until smooth, then add to beef mixture.
Remove 3 cups enchilada mix in medium size bowl.
Add other chopped onion.
Mix in 8 ounces of cheese. Place pan on fire with boiling water.
Dip 1 tortilla shell in water.
Remove, place in cake pan, put 2 tablespoons cheese in onion mixture in taco shell and roll.
Continue until all shells are done.
Pour remaining enchilada mixture over enchiladas. Sprinkle rest of cheese on top.
Place in oven until cheese melts and it bubbles.
You may put the tortilla shells on plates and place in oven until cheese melts.
Ready to eat.

title: apple cheese casserole
directions: Butter dish. Drain apples and layer in dish. Cream the butter, sugar, flour and cheese. Spread over apples.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: blueberry coffee cake
directions: In a bowl, beat eggs.
Add sugar and oil.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients.
Spread half of the dough in a greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Spread pie filling on top. Spread rest of dough on top. Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Drizzle with a powdered sugar glaze.

title: party ham sandwiches
directions: Combine ham, celery, dill pickle and mayonnaise or salad dressing.
Cover and chill.
Remove crusts from bread (if desired).
Spread white bread slices with ham mixture; top with rye bread slices.
Frost tops with cream cheese.
Cut each sandwich diagonally into quarters.
Decorate sandwiches with parsley or pimiento.
Makes 16 sandwiches.

title: out of this world eggplant
directions: Peel and cube eggplant and boil with small amount of water until tender; drain and mash. Add eggs, onion, salt, pepper, milk, corn bread crumbs, melted margarine and cheese. Mix well; pour into buttered casserole dish. Sprinkle top with buttered crumbs. Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix in order given in very large bowl.
Add nuts and raisins. Bake in a 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 3 (4 x 8-inch) loaf pans or 5 smaller loaf pans.
Test with a toothpick.
Cool, then slice.

title: cheesy green beans
directions: Cook bacon; drain and crumble bacon.
Cook beans; drain.
Add mushrooms and onions to skillet.
Cook and stir 10 minutes.
Add bacon, black pepper and hot green beans.
Mix
lightly.
Spoon into 2-quart baking dish.
Pour Cheese Whiz over mixture.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: ham and green bean bake
directions: Mix all together and sprinkle with crushed crackers.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: green corn tamales
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Place on clean husks (damp) by tablespoon.
Steam for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Mix together.
Place in ice cream freezer and freeze.

title: cheddar and macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain.
Brown beef with garlic, onions and peppers.
Drain off excessive fat. Stir in tomatoes with following seasonings:
basil, thyme, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in macaroni and half of the cheese.
Turn into a lightly greased 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cover top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 6 large servings.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix together hamburger, onion, salt and pepper; form into meatballs.
Cook the meatballs in the mixture of grape jelly and chili sauce at least 1/2 hour.

title: sugar cream pie
directions: Mix together and add 1 1/2 cups of cream.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: cranberry jelly salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water. Add cranberry jelly and cool. Beat with rotary until jelly is completely blended.
Mix pineapple and nuts.
Pour into mold and chill until firm.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine soup, melted butter and Cheez Whiz; stir together.
Add rice, then stir in broccoli.
Spray 9 x 9-inch dish with Pam.
Pour mixture into dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Put fried onions on top and cook 5 minutes more or until onions are golden brown.

title: raspberry-rhubarb jam
directions: Combine rhubarb, sugar and fresh lemon juice in a large pot or Dutch oven.
Cover and refrigerate 8 hours or overnight.
Juices will form.
Over medium heat, stir mixture to dissolve sugar and incorporate juices.
Increase heat to high and boil rhubarb mixture until slightly thickened, about 5 minutes.
Add raspberries; boil until thick, about 5 or 6 minutes longer.
May boil longer to further thicken, if desired.
Remove jam from heat; stir in cardamom.
Can be stored in the refrigerator, or you can ladle hot jam into clean, hot jars and process in a simmering water bath for 10 minutes.

title: chicken farfalle
directions: Boil water and soften the bowtie pasta.
Grill the chicken then chop into bite sized pieces. Dust the chicken lightly with basil.
Chop the garlic into fine pieces, slice the green pepper into long, narrow slices, and dice the onion.
In a pan or skillet, heat olive oil (cover the bottom of the pan) and add the garlic.
When garlic begins to simmer, add the spaghetti sauce. Cut the chicken in bite sized pieces.
Add to the sauce the rosemary, thyme, basil, oregano, salt, pepper and mushrooms.
When the sauce is bubbling, add the green peppers and onions.
Let it heat, then add the pasta and chicken.
Incorporate all ingredients together.
Serve hot.

title: beef mushroom loaf
directions: Mix all well together and bake at 325° for 60 minutes.
Freeze one for later if desired.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayo, sugar and vinegar; set aside.
Mix broccoli, onion and bacon. Add mayo mixture to the broccoli and mix well.
Add cheese and mix again.

title: lemon jello cake
directions: Beat all ingredients but oil together for two minutes.
Add oil and beat again for 2 minutes.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes, in loaf cake or tube pan.

title: ham salad sandwich(ham makes a great salad sandwich, also.)
directions: Drain the juice from the fruit, saving 1/2 cup of juice.
Mix cream cheese with this juice.
Dice the bananas, then mix all the ingredients together in a large bowl.
Place in a large pan or freezer container (square or oblong) about 1-inch high.
Freeze 2 hours or more.
Cut into squares and serve lightly thawed.
(Other fruit can be added.)
Serves 16 to 20.

title: sangria
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir.
Serve over ice.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Spread sauerkraut in the bottom of a 12 x 8-inch baking dish. Top with tomatoes.
Dot with dressing and butter.
Cover with corned beef.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in a 425° oven for 15 minutes.
Remove casserole from oven.
Separate each biscuit into three layers.
Slightly overlap biscuit layers on casserole to form three rows. Sprinkle with crackers and caraway seed.
Bake in 425° oven for 15 to 20 minutes until biscuits topping are golden brown.

title: oreo ice cream dessert
directions: Spray jello mold with Pam.
Alternate Oreos and ice milk layers.
Begin with cookies and end with cookies.
Put in freezer and freeze overnight.
Take out and turn over on plate.
Fill middle with Cool Whip.
Pour syrup over cake.
Add cherries.
You can make this diet by using low-fat cookies and light Cool Whip.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Preheat the oven to 375°.
Mix hominy, soup, chiles and sour cream.
Pour into casserole and bake for 30 minutes.
Top with cheese and bake 10 minutes more.
Serves 6.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all except nuts.
Chill.
Form ball or log, roll in nuts.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat sugar and shortening together and add eggs, one at a time. Beat well.
Add flour and spices; then add soda in hot water.
Add grated apples and nuts.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Ice while still warm with powdered sugar and water.

title: rainbow jello salad
directions: Use a 7 x 11-inch or 9 x 13-inch dish or pan.
Start with grape on bottom, then blueberry, lime, lemon, orange and red. Dissolve 1 cup boiling water with 1 package jello.
Divide this jello mixture in half.
To half, add 2 tablespoons cold water; to the other half, add 2 tablespoons sour cream and beat with fork. Pur clear grape jello in dish or pan.
Let set in refrigerator or freezer (about 20 minutes), then pour sour cream mixture on top and let set.
Repeat with rest of colors in the order given. Allow about 3 hours to make.
Do not cover until well set.

title: creole pork chops
directions: Salt and pepper the chops and place in a large skillet or Dutch oven.
Cover with rice, green peppers and onions.
Season with salt and pepper.
Combine boiling water and catsup.
Pour over chops and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 1 hour until chops and rice are tender.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Core head of cabbage.
Place in boiling water until leaves are pliable.
Remove from water and cool.
Place sauerkraut and ham or ribs in 4-quart pan on medium heat on top of stove.
In large mixing bowl, combine remaining ingredients until well blended. Take leaves apart from head of cabbage and place enough of meat mixture inside 1 leaf to make a roll (2 to 3 tablespoons).
Roll each leaf up, placing on top of sauerkraut.
If there is any cabbage left, cut up and put in with the sauerkraut also.
Cook 4 to 5 hours.

title: mom's goulash
directions: Brown hamburger and onion (drain fat).
Add tomato soup and sauce with 1 can of water.
Add garlic, basil, bouillon and bay leaves.
Add chopped carrots and corn.
Simmer 40 to 45 minutes (until carrots are done).

title: sugar free apple pie
directions: In saucepan, combine ingredients. Cook until apples start to soften. Pour into pie crust. Top with crust.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 425°.

title: microwave fudge pie
directions: In bowl, mix sugar, cocoa, flour and salt.
Place oleo in microwave-safe 2-cup glass container.
Microwave on High 30 to 45 seconds or until melted.
Add corn syrup, milk, eggs and vanilla. Stir well.
Add to dry mixture; blend.
Add pecans and pour into baked pie shell.
Microwave on Medium 12 to 14 minutes, rotating once midway through cooking.
Cool before cutting.

title: greek salad
directions: Combine all vegetables in large bowl and chill.
When ready to serve, beat olive oil and vinegar until smooth.
Pour over salad. Add oregano with salt and pepper to taste.
Toss salad until all particles are coated.
Serve at once.

title: mildred's ham roll-ups
directions: Mix well and spread on baked ham.
Roll and refrigerate. Slice when ready to serve.

title: leek and potato soup - 3 ways
directions: Remove root from leeks.
Cut white part and green part lengthwise and wash.
Slice whites and greens; keep separate. Have 3 cups leeks and/or onions.
Saute whites in butter.
Stir and cook slowly 5 to 6 minutes until soft but not browned.
Add flour to leek mixture.
Stir and cook 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add potatoes, water, salt and green of leeks.
Simmer, partly covered, 30 to 40 minutes.
Then add some milk.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg and butter into dough.
Spread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Combine confectioners sugar, 2 eggs and cream cheese, then pour over cake mix.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: country breakfast pie
directions: Cook sausage until done.
Crumble and drain.
Mix cheese and sausage.
Sprinkle in shell.
Combine other ingredients and add to egg mixture.
Pour into shell.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: apple crisp
directions: Toss fruit in sugar and spices, mixed.
Place in deep dish pie pan.
Dot surface with butter.

title: chili chicken
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles as directed on package; drain.
In large skillet, cook onion in butter until tender.
Stir in soup, pimentos and chili peppers.
In a greased 4-quart casserole, layer half the noodles and half the chicken; season with salt and pepper.
Pour half the soup mixture on chicken, then half the cheese.
Repeat layers and cover with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, about 45 minutes.
Makes 8 to 12 servings.

title: frozen heaven
directions: Cover the bottom of a 13 X 9 inch glass dish with ice cream sandwiches.
You may have to the last row to make them fit snugly. Spread about 1/4 inch cool whip on top of sandwiches.
Crumble the candy over the dish.
Place in freezer.
Cut into squares pieces and serve as an original homemade dessert.
your guests will be in awe of your ability to layer ice cream and chocolate. It is easier to cut up the candy cars if you freeze them first.

title: strawberry pecan cake
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients according to directions on cake mix.
Add berries, coconut and pecans.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes at 325°.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Stir together flour, sugar, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg, baking powder, salt and cloves in large bowl.
Lightly beat eggs.
Beat in pumpkin and oil.
Add to flour mixture, stirring just to combine.
Add raisins and walnuts.
Spoon into 2 greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pans.
Batter will be stiff.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until done.
Cool.
Remove from pans. Makes 2 loaves.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix oil, eggs, water and pumpkin together, set aside.
Grease and flour 1 Bundt pan.
Mix together flour, sugar, salt, nutmeg, cinnamon and baking soda.
Add dry ingredients to liquid; mix well.
Add nuts and raiains.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or more, keep checking.

title: summer salad
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Cook beans until tender but firm.
Mix desired amount of vegetables into bowl.
Add grated cheese and dressing; mix well.
Refrigerate until cold.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter, sugar and salt.
Add well-beaten eggs, syrup, nuts and vanilla.
Mix well and put in raw pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour (approximately); do not overbake.

title: coconut pie
directions: Melt butter.
Beat eggs with a fork.
Add sugar and stir.
Add buttermilk, butter and vanilla.
Mix well.
Stir in coconut. Pour in pie crusts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: nachos
directions: Cook first three ingredients until meat is done.
Drain grease off.
Add 1 can refried beans to ground beef mixture.
Into 9 x 13-inch casserole dish spread layers of:
taco corn chips, meat mixture (thick and needs to be spread), chopped fresh tomatoes, small can taco sauce, layer of sharp Cheddar cheese, layer of taco chips, layer of sharp Cheddar cheese.
Bake uncovered at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cornbread casserole
directions: Do this in the order given.
Then top with cooked tomatoes and season to taste.
Bake at 325° until done.

title: beata sweet pickles
directions: Wash and cut cucumbers into chunks.
Pack into quart jars and add to each jar the spices, etc.
Fill up jars with water.
Place lid on jars.
Let them stand in cool place 3 months or longer. When ready to use, drain off liquid and rinse well.
Add 1/2 cup sugar per jar.
Mix well.
Let set 3 days, then they are ready.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: In medium skillet, cut up undrained tomatoes. Add next 6 ingredients. Add 1/2 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper. Place chicken atop. Bring to a boil. Simmer, covered, 25 minutes. Remove chicken. Sprinkle with paprika and keep warm. Combine cornstarch and 2 tablespoons cold water. Stir into skillet mixture. Cook and stir until thickened. Cook 1 minute longer. Spoon sauce over chicken. If desired, garnish with a sprig of parsley. Yield: 4 servings.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 9-inch pie pan.
Beat all ingredients until smooth.
Beat 2 minutes with hand beater.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake until knife comes out clean in center of pie (50 to 55 minutes).
No crust needed.

title: black walnut pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and flavorings. Fold in flour, baking powder and salt.
Add milk.
Mix nuts with a little flour and add to mixture.
Pour into floured and greased tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 80 minutes.

title: pink arctic freeze
directions: Soften cheese and blend in mayonnaise and sugar.
Add fruits and nuts.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into loaf pan (8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch).
Freeze firm 6 hours or overnight.

title: cranberry muffins(a cape cod recipe)
directions: Mix cranberries with powdered sugar. Mix together dry ingredients. Add egg, milk and margarine and mix until moistened. Fold in cranberries.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: pizza cracker spread
directions: Cream together cream cheese, onion, garlic salt and seasoned salt.
Spread on round plate or pizza pan.
Spread barbecue sauce over cheese mixture.
Top all of this with the clams or crab meat. Sprinkle with oregano.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Saute onion and celery in 2 tablespoons oleo.
Combine broccoli, broth and water in a 4-quart pot.
Bring to boil and cook until broccoli is tender.
Add cream, onions, celery and ham. Add flour to thicken and salt to taste.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Grease and flour tube pan.
Cream first 4 ingredients.
Add remainder of ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in 2 tablespoons margarine.
Stir in tuna, soup, mayonnaise, milk and mushrooms.
Cook noodles and drain.
Combine all in 2-quart greased casserole.
Top with bread crumbs topped with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pizza pie
directions: In a bowl, mix meat loaf according to directions on recipe. Press into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake until almost done. Remove from oven. Spread with spaghetti sauce and Mozzarella cheese. Return to oven until cheese is melted.
Let set 5 minutes before serving.

title: corn bread taco bake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a large skillet, brown ground beef. Drain.
Stir in taco seasoning, water, corn, green pepper and tomato sauce.
Pour mixture into 2-quart casserole.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Put butter, brown sugar and pineapple to melt in an iron frying pan.
Mix white sugar, flour, egg yolks, vanilla and baking powder in a bowl with pineapple juice.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into batter. Pour batter over pineapple in skillet. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: marie's roast
directions: Put all ingredients in a crock-pot.
Cook on high for 6 to 7 hours.
Serves 4.

title: fruit slush
directions: Mix in blender all except strawberries and water.
Mix in an ice cream pail and place in freezer for 12 hours.

title: cinnamon date squares
directions: Combine dates, 2 tablespoons sugar and 1/2 cup water in saucepan.
Simmer until dates are soft, about 3 minutes.
Stir in 1/4 teaspoon vanilla.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Beat 3/4 cup sugar into butter, then egg, 1/2 teaspoon vanilla and finally the flour mixture.
Wrap and chill.
Between 2 sheets of wax paper, roll out half the dough to a 9-inch square and put into a buttered 9-inch pan.
Spread with dates.
Roll out remaining dough and put on top.
Press edges with fork and vent. Brush with milk and sprinkle with 1 tablespoon sugar.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until golden.
Cool; cut into bars.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Stir together peanuts, sugar and Karo in 1 1/2-quart glass casserole.
Microwave on full power 8 to 9 minutes.
Stir after 4 minutes.
Add butter, soda and vanilla.
Pour onto buttered cookie sheet.
Cool and break into pieces.
Yields 1 pound.

title: jiffy chicken or turkey pie
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Blend in flour and stir until frothy. Add soup.
Heat until thickened.
Add chicken, seasonings and vegetables.
Heat thoroughly.
Pour into a greased shallow 3-quart casserole.
Arrange biscuits on top.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes or until biscuits are brown.

title: broccoli noodle soup
directions: Saute the onion in oleo.
Bring to a boil the chicken bouillon cubes and water.
Add noodles, broccoli, cheese and milk.
Cook until noodles are tender and broccoli done.
Enjoy.

title: coffee can bread
directions: You will need 2 (1 pound) coffee cans.

title: fresh strawberry pie 2
directions: Mix together in saucepan, sugar, boiling water and cornstarch. Bring to a boil; remove from heat.
Add jello; stir and chill. Clean and pat dry the strawberries.
Place in a pie shell.
Pour cooled mixture over fruit.
When set, decorate with Cool Whip and some fresh strawberries.

title: little ham biscuits
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients until margarine has melted. Slice party rolls in half.
Spread mixture on rolls.
Slice cheese and ham to fit rolls.
Bake at 325° until cheese is slightly melted.

title: mushroom soup
directions: Saute mushrooms, garlic and scallions in margarine.
Add flour and soup which has been blended together.
Simmer for 20 minutes; add cream just before serving.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream the sugar and Crisco together.
Mix in well beaten eggs. Mash 3 bananas separately and add to mixture, then add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Pour into bread pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese pie
directions: Mix graham crackers, sugar and melted butter together.
Place in a 7 to 8-inch pie pan.
Press to shape of pan using back of spoon.

title: lemon bars
directions: Blend
1 cup flour, 1/2 cup butter and 1/4 cup powdered sugar as for pastry; press into 8-inch square pan, ungreased. Bake
for
minutes.
Combine eggs, sugar, baking powder, lemon juice and 2 tablespoons flour.
Pour onto bottom layer and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool slightly.

title: sawdust pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix well, but do not beat.
Turn into pie shell and bake until filling is set (about 35 minutes).
Do not overbake.
Serve at room temperature.
Garnish each serving with a mound of Cool Whip.
Put 2 slices of banana and a red cherry on each serving.

title: apple cranberry pie
directions: In a large bowl, mix together the sugars, flour and cinnamon. Add the apples and cranberries and mix to coat well.
Turn into a pastry-lined 9-inch pie pan.
Dot with margarine.
Cover with top crust and seal.
Cut small slits in top crust for steam to escape. Bake at 400° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients and press into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Allow to cool. Mix next 3 ingredients and spread over crust.
Mix pudding according to box directions.
Spread over cream cheese layer. Spread Cool Whip over chocolate layer.
Top with grated chocolate. Chill overnight.

title: baked round steak
directions: Saute onion in Crisco until light brown; remove from skillet. Cut steak into serving pieces, flour and brown where onion was sauteed.
Add salt and pepper and remove meat from skillet.
Put meat in a small roaster or covered dish.
Add enough water and flour in skillet to make 2 cups of thin brown gravy.
Add catsup and Worcestershire sauce.
Spread onion over steak and pour gravy over the top.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours or until tender.

title: mississippi mud
directions: Combine eggs and sugar.
Beat well.
Combine melted oleo, flour, vanilla, nuts and coconut which makes a mud mixture.
Add to egg mix.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
When done, remove from oven.
Top with Marshmallow Creme while still hot.
(You could also use peanut butter instead of Marshmallow Creme.)

title: luby's old-fashioned egg salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine lettuce, half the eggs, half the onions and half the olives. Garnish with remaining eggs, onions and olives. Cover and chill.

title: dill weed dip(for fresh veggies)
directions: Blend all ingredients until smooth.
Chill.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: baked eggplant souffle(the wyatt's recipe)
directions: Soak eggplant pieces in salted water in refrigerator for several hours or overnight. Do not skip this step. Soak bread crumbs in both types of milk.
Saute pepper, onion and celery in margarine until tender.
Drain salt water from eggplant. Cover with fresh water and boil until nearly tender; drain well.
Mix eggplant, bread, sauteed veggies, eggs, pepper, sage and pimento in medium size mixing bowl.
Place in greased 2 1/2-quart casserole. Top with cheese and bake in a 350° oven until golden brown, 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: fluff dip for fruit
directions: Mix pudding mix, milk and Triple Sec. Beat in thawed whipped topping. Chill 1 hour. Serve with fruit.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Drain all vegetables.
Boil together sugar, vinegar and oil. Cool and mix with vegetables.
Refrigerate overnight.
This keeps well for several days.

title: creamy chicken primavera
directions: In a large skillet, melt butter.
Add chicken.
Cook until no longer pink.
Add pasta and vegetables package and water.
Cook covered over medium heat for 7 to 9 minutes.
Stir occasionally. Stir in sour cream and heat thoroughly.
Yields 4 servings.

title: low-fat macaroni and cheese
directions: In large casserole, mix cooked macaroni, pot cheese (not cottage cheese), eggs, milk and salt.
Top with dabs of low-fat margarine or butter.
Bake at 350° until top is nicely browned.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage; drain fat off.
Use a long 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Place meat on bottom layer.
Spread sauce over meat.
Spread cheese over sauce.

title: old-fashioned fried pies
directions: Place biscuit mix and milk in a large mixing bowl; stir well to combine.
Shape dough into a ball.
Cover dough and chill thoroughly.
Roll chilled dough to 1/8 inch thickness on a lightly floured surface.
Cut 10 (4 inch) circles from dough.
Place about 1 1/2 tablespoons pie filling in center of each circle of dough. Moisten edges with water.
Fold dough over pie filling to form half circles.
Seal edges of dough securely with a fork.
Chill prepared pies 30 minutes.

title: saucy cube steak
directions: Season cube steaks and brown quickly on both sides in hot oil. Remove steak.
Saute onion, green pepper and mushrooms in browned drippings until tender.
Stir in chili sauce and juice.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Return steaks to sauce, spoon sauce on top, cover and heat thoroughly.
Extra juice and chili sauce may not be added.

title: microwave pralines
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine sugar and cream, stirring well. Microwave on High power 14 minutes, stirring after 7 minutes.
Add butter and pecans.
Microwave on High power 1 to 2 minutes or until a few drops of the mixture will form a soft ball in a cup of cold water.
Working quickly, drop by large tablespoonfuls onto wax paper.
If necessary, return bowl to microwave for a few minutes to soften the mixture.
Let stand to harden about 30 minutes.

title: hot spice tea
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Use 2 to 3 teaspoons per cup of hot water.
Additional sugar may be added, if desired.
Store mix in airtight container.

title: creamy chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Mix all ingredients in a bowl. Pour over chicken.
Cook until chicken is done.
The soups will make a delicious gravy, which may be served over mashed potatoes or rice.
Cook at 350°.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: western potato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour one 10-cup tube pan or two large loaf pans.
Sprinkle with cinnamon sugar.
Pour batter into prepared pans and bake for 60 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes. Remove from pan.
This freezes well.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Layer first 4 ingredients in oblong casserole dish.
Layer crumbled bacon over vegetables.
Add peas.
Spread mayonnaise with sugar over salad.
Top with grated cheese.
Refrigerate 24 hours.

title: no bake chocolate peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine sugar, milk and cocoa in saucepan and bring to a boil. Cook 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients. Stir and mix well. Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper. Let stand for 30 minutes before serving.

title: strawberry cheese bars
directions: Combine flour and brown sugar.
Cut in Crisco until fine crumbs form.
Add nuts and coconut; mix well.
Press crumbs in bottom of greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes until edges are lightly browned.

title: grandmother's devil's food cake
directions: Blend in order and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until sides pull away from pan and cake springs back at touch.
Not required but insert cake tester to be sure that it's done.

title: chocolate eclair dessert
directions: Beat well and pour over top of grahams.
Refrigerate 24 to 48 hours.
Serves 12.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Chop all ingredients very fine and blend with the mayonnaise. Stir in mustard and Tabasco.
Chill thoroughly for several hours so that flavors will be well blended.

title: cherry cheesecake tarts
directions: You will also need small cupcake papers.

title: broccoli puff
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Butter souffle dish (1 1/2-quart).
Cook broccoli and drain.
Beat eggs, milk, Bisquick and salt with hand mixer until smooth.
Stir in broccoli and cheese. Bake about 1 hour or until knife comes out clean.
Serve immediately.

title: rainbow cake
directions: Combine cake mix, sour cream, water and eggs.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Spoon 1/3 cup batter into Bundt cake pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 package jello and repeat layers.
Spread remaining batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: spinach and cheese calzone
directions: Cook and drain spinach thoroughly.
In a frypan, cook garlic. Add spinach, oil and pepperoni; stir together.
Keep on low heat. Spread 1 loaf dough on cookie sheet.
Add spinach mixture on top. Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Place same size dough on top. Seal very tightly.
Press air out.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes until golden.

title: delicious apple cake
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.

title: chicken and sausage gumbo
directions: Saute sausage in oil until brown, using a 12-quart stock pot. Remove from pot.
Season chicken with a little cayenne, salt and a dusting of flour.
Brown in the oil and remove from the pot.
Make a roux by slowly adding 1 cup flour to the hot oil in pot.
Stir constantly over medium heat.
Roux must be a dark brown, but not allowed to burn.
When desired color is achieved, add onions, celery, green peppers, parsley and garlic all at once to stop roux from cooking further.
Cook until glaze forms on vegetables.
They should be slightly tender.
Return sausage and chicken to pot and cook a few minutes on low heat.
Gradually stir in broth and bring to a boil.
Reduce to simmer and cook 1 hour more.
Serve with some good bread for dipping.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients. Add oil, eggs, bananas and pineapple. Do not beat the mixture. Bake in 3 layers at 350° for 30 minutes. Cool cake layers, then frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: glitter torte
directions: Prepare jello separately, except lemon, using 1 cup hot water to each package of jello, then add 1/2 cup cold water to each. Pour into separate pans and chill overnight.

title: scottish mincemeat
directions: Brown meat while stirring constantly to break it into fine particles.
Add finely chopped onion, salt, pepper and water. Cover and simmer gently for 30 minutes.
Serve with boiled or mashed potatoes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Blend mayonnaise and sugar into softened cream cheese.
Add fruit and nuts, then fold in cream which has been whipped and to which the powdered sugar and vanilla have been added.
Pour into a large rectangular pan or glass dish.
Freeze at least 6 hours before serving.

title: kona banana bread and muffins
directions: Beat first three ingredients together. Add mashed bananas and remainder of ingredients. Bake at 350° for 50-60 minutes. Test for doneness with toothpick in center. For muffins bake approximately 25 minutes.

title: cream cheese cake
directions: Butter tube pan and put graham cracker crumbs on bottom, or you can substitute pound cake crumbs for graham cracker crumbs; it works better.

title: crawfish spaghetti
directions: Thaw crawfish and rinse.
Saute onion, bell pepper, and celery in butter.
Add cream of mushroom soup, Velveeta, and both cans of Rotel.
Can use two regular Rotel in place of the hot one, depending on how spicy you want it.
Add crawfish when you put your water on to boil for spaghetti.

title: instant twice baked potatoes
directions: Make instant potatoes according to directions on package (6 to 8 serving size).
After potatoes are cooked, add sour cream, 1 1/2 cups of shredded cheese and seasonings; mix well and put into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle remaining cheese over potatoes; put into a 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Melt butter in dish.
Mix with flour and pecans well.
Press down in bottom of dish.
Bake until lightly browned in oven at 350°.
Let crust cool.

title: chicken cheese soup
directions: Remove boiled chicken from broth and bone it.
To broth, add carrots, onion, celery and potatoes.
Cook until tender.
In another pot, mix milk, butter and cornstarch.
Add cheese.
Cook until cheese melts.
Add to broth.
Season with salt and pepper. Freezes well.

title: walnut cake
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Stir in other ingredients, saving half the nuts and 2 egg whites for the icing and using half the nuts in the cake batter.
Bake in four layers for 20 to 25 minutes at 375°.

title: apple cake pie
directions: Place apples in greased 9 or 10-inch pie plate and sprinkle with 1/4 cup sugar and 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon.
Cover tightly with foil and bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Remove from oven. Reduce heat to 375°.
Mix remaining ingredients well to form a batter and cover apple mixture.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: flavorful tuna salad
directions: Set aside 10 olives.
Chop remaining olives.
Combine tuna, chopped olives and celery.
Combine mayonnaise, lemon juice, mustard, onion powder and ginger.
Mix well.
Pour over tuna mixture.
Stir gently and chill until serving time.
If desired, serve on lettuce leaves.
Garnish with reserved olives.
Yields 10 servings.

title: egg-sausage casserole
directions: Cook sausage until browned; drain off fat.
In a saucepan, melt 1/4 cup butter; stir in flour and salt.
Add milk all at once.
Cook and stir 1 to 2 minutes more.
Stir in cooked sausage and sliced eggs.
Pour mixture into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Toss bread crumbs with melted butter and sprinkle atop casserole. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through. Makes 6 servings.

title: kolaches(easy does it)
directions: In small bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water.
Sprinkle in 1 tablespoon sugar.
Let stand.
Scald milk in saucepan.
Remove from heat and stir in butter and 1/2 cup sugar.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add salt and egg yolks.
Combine milk mixture and yeast in a large bowl.
Add flour in small amounts to milk mixture until all flour has been used.
Knead dough on lightly floured board until glossy. Place in bowl; cover and let rise in warm place until doubled in size, about 1 hour.
Punch down.
Shape into ball, about 3-inches. Press on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until brown, about 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions.

title: old fashion pound cake
directions: Mix ingredients in order given and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes or until the cake comes away from the sides.

title: easy hamburger-vegetable soup
directions: Empty mixed vegetables, tomato juice and spaghetti sauce into large pan.
Peel and dice potatoes and put with vegetables.
Add salt and pepper.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Brown hamburger; drain and add to vegetables.
To thicken soup, add 1 to 2 cups of instant potatoes.
Cook additional 10 minutes.
Serves 20 people.

title: sour cream pie
directions: Mix all together, except Cool Whip,
and pour into baked pie shell.
Refrigerate.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: chicken breasts
directions: Place chicken in a baking dish; top with soup and water. Cover chicken with slices of cheese and top with stuffing mix. Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together, making a batter.
Pour into a baking dish and add (can be mixed in the baking dish) fruit (cherries, peaches, blackberries or fruit in season).
Bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes or until light brown.

title: chocolate chip party cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat together sugars and butter until light and fluffy.
Blend eggs and vanilla.
Add combined flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 6 dozen, 2 1/2-inch cookies.

title: barbecued beef sandwiches
directions: Simmer 3 to 4 hours.
Mash by hand with potato masher.
Serve on hamburger bun or similar.

title: saturday supper salad
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients. Blend mayonnaise and French dressing. Toss lightly. Add salt and serve on lettuce.
Garnish with sliced hard-cooked egg.

title: pork chop onion-rice
directions: Brown pork chops.
Spread rice in bottom of rectangular baking dish (13 1/2 x 9 x 2-inch).
Reserve 1 tablespoon of seasonings from envelope of onion soup mix.
Drain mushrooms, reserving liquid.
Add hot water to reserved mushroom liquid to total 3 cups liquid.
Dissolve remaining onion soup mix in liquid.
Add mushrooms; pour over rice.
Arrange browned pork chops on top of rice mixture; sprinkle chops with reserved seasonings.
Cover tightly with foil; bake in moderate oven (350°) until tender, for 45 minutes to 1 hour, depending upon thickness of chops.
Remove foil; continue cooking for 10 minutes or longer, or until any excess liquid evaporates.
Makes 6 servings.

title: dr. zan's texas barbecued beef
directions: Get a thick brisket (more than 1-inch thick) with a good rind of fat (the fat is essential).
Tenderize several hours before doing anything else.
Just before cooking, sprinkle with a little chili and garlic powders and salt and pepper and rub in.

title: hawaiian banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add bananas and eggs.
Sift flour, salt and baking soda 3 times.
Blend flour mixture into banana mixture.
Do not overmix.
Turn batter into 2 greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for 55 minutes or until toothpick tests dry in center of loaf.
Turn out immediately to cool on wire rack.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: burnt sugar icing
directions: In heavy
saucepan, cook 1/2 cup sugar to liquid stage. Add 1/2 cup
water
and
melt
again.
Add 3 cups sugar, light corn syrup, cream and
salt.
Cook
without
stirring until it forms a soft ball.	Add
butter.
After
it
cools,
whip with mixer until creamy, 5 to
8 minutes.
Store in icebox 8 hours. Melt (may use microwave) and spread on layers.

title: broccoli-corn casserole
directions: Place broccoli in a shallow 1 quart microwavable dish.
Cover with a glass lid or plastic wrap, turning 1 edge back.
Microwave at 100% power for 4 to 5 minutes or until no longer icy, stirring after 2 minutes.
Drain well; set aside.
Microwave margarine in a 2-cup Pyrex bowl at 100% for 45 to 60 seconds or until melted. Stir in stuffing mix until well coated.
Stir the corn, 1/2 cup of the buttered stuffing mix, onion salt and pepper into the broccoli until well blended.
Microwave uncovered at 100% power for 3 minutes.
Stir, then sprinkle remaining stuffing mix over top and sprinkle with paprika.
Microwave at 100% power for 3 to 4 minutes or until heated.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Cook green pepper and mushrooms in butter until tender; blend in flour and salt.
Add broth and milk.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add pimiento and chicken; heat to blend flavors.
Pour over hot biscuits or patty shells, etc.
Yields 6 servings.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on box.
In a buttered 11 x 13-inch pan, spread coconut and pecans.
Melt oleo; blend with softened cream cheese, then gradually add sugar.
Beat until smooth; dot this mixture on top of cake batter.
Bake about 55 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate haystacks
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, cocoa, milk and butter; bring to full boil. Remove from heat. Stir in remaining ingredients. Drop by spoonful on waxed paper and let cool.

title: coffee punch
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and cool. Soften ice cream and add to mixture. Serves 45.

title: mary's meat loaf
directions: Mix together ground sirloin, bread crumbs, green pepper, onion, egg, salt and 4 ounces tomato sauce. Shape into loaf in baking pan.
Mix together 4 ounces tomato sauce, water, brown sugar, vinegar and mustard.
Pour over meat loaf.
Baste during cooking. Bake at 350° for about 1 1/4 hours.

title: sombero meat balls
directions: Mix gravy as directed; set aside.
Mix all ingredients with hands until well mixed.
Form into meat balls the size of cherry tomatoes.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes or until light brown.
Drain.

title: onion casserole
directions: Peel and slice onions; cut into rings.
Saute in butter or margarine.
Place in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Cover with crushed Ritz crackers.
Sprinkle on Parmesan cheese.
Dot with butter or margarine.
Bake at 350° approximately 20 minutes.

title: golden potato soup
directions: Mix first eight ingredients together in just enough boiling water to cover, cooking until vegetables are tender, about 10 minutes.
Whisk together milk and flour and stir into the vegetables.
Then add cheese.
Stir until cheese is melted.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
