Heat and serve with cake or cookies.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Season sufficient amount of flour for amount of chicken being used with pepper and seasoned salt in a bowl.
Dredge chicken in flour mixture thoroughly.

Dip floured chicken into bowl of evaporated milk to which a small amount of oil has been added. Roll chicken in crushed corn flake crumbs, which are made by crumbling corn flake cereal in the blender or food processor. Place pieces in lightly oiled (1/4-inch) pan with the breast side up.
Bake in slow oven (300°), uncovered, for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until well browned.
Remove from oven before crumbs become burned looking around the edges.

title: souper scalloped potatoes
directions: Blend soup, milk and pepper well.
Arrange thinly sliced potatoes and onion in a casserole dish and pour soup mixture over top.
Drizzle with melted butter and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in 375 degree oven for 1 hour.

title: chicken casserole i
directions: Place cooked chicken in greased baking dish; add salt and pepper.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Pour over top of chicken; crumble crackers on top and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: hot crab dip
directions: In large bowl, mix first 8 ingredients, adding enough milk to make it creamy.
Stir in 2 tablespoons of cheese.
Fold in crab meat into the mixture.
Pour into greased casserole, 1 quart size. Top with remaining cheese and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 325° until bubbly and brown, about 30 minutes.

title: chocolate truffles
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Roll into ball shapes.
Roll truffles in coconut or chopped nuts.
Keep refrigerated.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in Dutch oven; cover and simmer 15 minutes or until tender.
Remove from heat.
Pour one-half of mixture into an electric blender and puree until smooth.
Return mixture to pan.
Repeat procedure with remaining broccoli mixture. Add remaining ingredients to pureed mixture and heat thoroughly (do not boil).

title: mock chicken
directions: Brown hamburger and mix with crumbled bread.
Add soup and milk and mix well.
Season with salt and pepper.
Bake in a greased baking dish at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: gourmet ginger muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine ginger root with 1/4 cup sugar over medium
heat until sugar is melted, stirring constantly in heavy skillet or pan.
Let cool.
Stir in lemon rind.
Cream butter and 1/2 cup sugar.
Beat until smooth.
Beat in eggs and buttermilk.
Add flour, salt and soda.
Beat until just smooth. Stir in ginger mixture.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 16 muffins.

title: corned beef hash
directions: Fry onion and fatback until limp.
Then add potatoes and fry until browned, stirring often.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve over rice and grits.

title: viva italian cold spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti as directed.
Drain and rinse in cold water. In large bowl, pour dressing.
Chop up tomatoes, green pepper and onion.
Stir into dressing.
Add cayenne pepper and add spaghetti; stir until coated.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: pudding pie
directions: In large bowl, prepare pudding as package directions using the 2 cups milk.
Fold in the butter and whipped topping.
Pour into pie crust.
Refrigerate 4 hours or until firm.
Top with toasted coconut or banana slices, etc.

title: pinto bean casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and green pepper.
Blend in tomato sauce, chili powder and salt.
In greased 2-quart casserole dish, layer part of meat sauce, beans and 1/2 cheese.
Then put another layer of meat and top with rest of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pecan pralines
directions: Cook on low fire the sugar and buttermilk until it forms soft ball, stirring occasionally.
Add the soda and stir a few strokes. Add vanilla and margarine and stir until beginning to thicken. Drop by spoon on wax paper. Will have to work very fast or last of candy will be too hard to drop.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and water together.
Bring to a rolling boil. Remove from heat.
Beat in the peanut butter until creamy.
Pour into an 8-inch square pan, lightly buttered.
Do not overcook.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix Jell-O with 1 cup boiling water and add cold water. Add ginger ale	cranberry
and pineapple juice.
Stir well and add ice.

title: no-fat fruit salad
directions: Drain off fruit juice.
Pour Jell-O powder over fruit and mix well.
Refrigerate.
May top with Cool Whip or coconut or strawberries.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain meat.
Add tomato sauce and garlic powder.
Cook on low while preparing noodles.
Boil water and cook noodles according to package directions.

title: squash balls
directions: Mix all ingredients except white bread crumbs.
Roll into balls, then roll in white bread crumbs.
Drop in deep fat fryer until golden brown.
(Should look like hushpuppies.)

title: no bake chocolate cake
directions: Whip the egg whites and sugar until stiff.
Melt chocolate and mix in egg yolks and milk. Fold all ingredients together and place in spring-form pan.
Refrigerate overnight.
Top with whipped cream (optional).
Serves 15 to 20.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix apples, sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla; sift in flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Mix all together.
Pour in greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mom's beef stew
directions: Place soup bones and water in a soup kettle or Dutch oven. Slowly bring to boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 2 hours. Set beef bones aside until cool enough to handle.
Remove meat from bones; discard bones and return meat to broth.
Add the potatoes, carrots, onion, barley, tomatoes, salt, pepper, garlic, and bay leaf if desired.
Cover and simmer for 50-60 minutes or until vegetables and barley are tender.
Discard bay leaf.
Combine cornstarch and cold water until smooth; stir into stew.
Bring o boil; cook and stir for 2 minutes or until thickened.
Yield:
10 servings.

title: pearl's homemade chili
directions: Brown the ground beef.
Drain.
Add onion.
Combine all other ingredients until well heated.

title: cabbage-bacon slaw
directions: Cabbage should be very thinly sliced or shredded. Place into large mixing bowl. Add celery, cucumber, green pepper and green onions. Sprinkle with half the parsley. Fold in the bacon.

title: hawaiian pudding
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and melted margarine.
Spread in bottom of sheet pan or Tupperware container.
Pat down.
Slice 3 bananas and put on top of crumbs.
Mix milk and lemon juice.
Pour on top of bananas.
Spread pineapple (well drained) over top. Sprinkle 1 cup coconut over the pineapple.
Add chopped pecans over the coconut.
Cover the top with Cool Whip.
You may add a small amount of coconut and pecans on top, if desired.
Cover and store in refrigerator.

title: danish pudding cake
directions: Beat butter in a large bowl at medium speed.
Gradually add 1 3/4 cups sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Combine flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk, beginning with flour.
Stir in pecans and next 3 ingredients.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour (do not remove cake from pan).

title: cedar lakes dressing
directions: Cover and blend at high speed for 20 seconds.

title: margaret's carrot cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil. Sift flour, soda, salt and cinnamon together twice. Add eggs to sugar mixture, one at a time.
Add flour to mixture, then carrots and mix. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes. Makes 3 layers.

title: peanut butter sticks
directions: Heat oven to 350°; toast bread.
Cut 6 slices into 8 sticks each.
Crush 2 slices into crumbs.
Prepare peanut butter with oil.
Heat and stir until soft.
Dip sticks into this while warm. Roll in crumbs.
Store in ziploc bag.

title: lazy pie
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish.
Combine sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and milk.
Pour over butter.
Do not stir.
Cover with fruit.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Fruit can be on top or bottom.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate and butter over low heat.
Remove from heat and blend in milk; set aside.
Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Blend in chocolate mixture.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Combine pecans and coconut.
Sprinkle evenly over pie.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Put first 3 ingredients in a microwave-safe bowl.
Cook 3 minutes on High.
Remove and add sugar.
Blend and pat into a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Put in a refrigerator to cool.
Cut in squares.

title: house dressing
directions: Combine ingredients and you have a delicious Thousand Island house dressing.

title: mom's bread pudding
directions: Beat eggs with beater. Fold into other ingredients. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: rice krispie bars
directions: Mix peanut butter and corn syrup in 6-quart kettle on medium heat just until warm.
Add Rice Krispies; pour into buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread evenly.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large container.
Be sure to blend it in well.
For a cup of hot chocolate, use 3 to 4 teaspoons of mix to a cup of boiling water.

title: candied dill pickles
directions: Heat to
boiling and pour over dill pickles that have been sliced lengthwise into strips.

title: homemade salsa
directions: Just chop and mix all ingredients together.
Best made the night before serving.
Easy to double for a crowd.
Serve with chips or crackers.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix in order given and bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until brown on top.

title: sara's russian tea
directions: Mix ingredients.
Use 4 teaspoons per 1 cup of hot water. Great winter treat!

title: cheese potatoes
directions: In large bowl, separate potatoes.
Melt margarine or butter and pour over potatoes.
In another bowl, mix the other ingredients and pour over potatoes and mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: mint-roasted onions
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Line bottom of 8-inch baking pan with foil.
Cut onions in half crosswise; remove skins.
Place, cut side down, in pan.
Whisk remaining ingredients in small bowl until well blended; drizzle over onions.
Lift onions and swirl in liquid so cut sides are moistened.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour or until onions are tender and golden brown, basting with pan drippings several times during roasting.
(During end of baking, liquid evaporates and cut sides of onions become glazed.)
Serve onion halves cut side up.
Serves 4.

title: pear bread
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together.
Add oil and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add sour cream.
Fold in pears and nuts. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown beef and drain off fat.
Add tomatoes and cook until thick, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Put potatoes, onions and pepper in an oblong baking dish.
Pour beef sauce over vegetables and salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and cook in a preheated 350° oven for about 40 to 45 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Yields 3 to 4 servings.

title: pork igado
directions: Cut pork into small thin slices, separating the fat from the meat.
Cut liver in a separate container.
Brown fat of pork; add chopped up garlic and brown.
Add chopped up meat and saute with oyster sauce; stir occasionally for 1/2 hour or until meat is cooked.
On a separate dish, soak liver with 2 tablespoons vinegar and ground pepper; mix to cook meat.
Add food coloring (achuete) and salt to taste.
Simmer for another 10 minutes.
(Food coloring is optional.)
Serves 4.

title: burnt sugar cake
directions: Mix and sift flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Cream butter or margarine and sugar.
Add egg and yolk.
Beat until smooth and light.
Add water alternately with dry ingredients.
Add Burnt Sugar Syrup.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 8-inch pans. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Use the recipe for the Burnt Sugar Icing to frost the cake.

title: skywalker scrunchies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Use lightly greased cookie sheet. Cream butter and sugar; beat in egg and vanilla.
Slowly add flour, then add corn flakes; mix well.
Drop level tablespoons onto greased cookie sheet, about 3 inches apart.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes, or until golden brown around edges.
Yields 25 cookies.

title: "sure losers" vegetable soup
directions: Add any other vegetables you like.

title: hash brown chicken casserole
directions: Mix together first 8 ingredients. Place in large baking dish. Melt margarine and toss with corn flakes and sprinkle on casserole. Lightly cover with foil for first half hour of baking. Bake in 350 degree oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours until bubbly and potatoes are done.

title: two egg yellow cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 9-inch round cake pans or one 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Into large bowl measure all ingredients; with mixer at low speed, beat until well mixed, constantly scraping bowl with rubber spatula.
Beat at medium speed 4 minutes, occasionally scraping bowl.
Pour batter into pans and bake round layers 30 to 35 minutes, until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool cake in pans on wire racks 10 minutes; remove from pans and cool completely on wire racks.
Makes 2 layers or 1 cake.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Blend oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir dry ingredients. Combine all ingredients together.
Spread in a 13 x 9-inch greased pan.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: bill's best waffles
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Beat egg yolks, add to milk and melted butter.
Make hole in center of dry ingredients; dribble milk mixture.
Fold in, do not beat.
(Do this just before cooking.)
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Cook waffles on preheated waffle iron (Vitantanio iron preferred) just before serving.
Serve with maple syrup.
Makes 2 waffles.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Dust apples, nuts and raisins with flour; set aside.
Mix oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla together.
Beat well.
Sift dry ingredients together; add to egg mixture.
Mix well.
Add apples, nuts and raisins.
Stir well and pour into greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: stephen's broccoli salad
directions: Mix all the salad ingredients together.

title: polka dot bars
directions: Cream together first 3 ingredients. Beat in eggs and vanilla. Stir in heaping cup flour, then chocolate chips. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: tangy sweet and sour sauce
directions: Mix cornstarch and brown sugar in saucepan.
Stir in vinegar, teriyaki sauce and pineapple.
Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer for about 2 minutes.
Makes approximately 2 1/2 cups.
Good with beef, pork and chicken that has been grilled or baked.

title: irish chocolate (diet-sugar-free)
directions: In small saucepan, mix water and Alba '66 milk chocolate flavor.
Cook, stirring occasionally, over low heat until mixture is smooth and hot.
Pour 1/2 cup hot chocolate into each of 4 (8 ounce) warmed, stemmed glasses.
Add 1 teaspoon brown sugar to each serving.
Stir gently until sugar is dissolved.
Add 1 tablespoon whiskey to each glass.
Top each serving with 1 tablespoon whipped topping.
Makes 4 drinks.

title: cheese-sausage biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: lena's quickie pie
directions: Melt butter or margarine in 8 x 12-inch pan.
Mix flour, 1/2 cup sugar and milk to make dough.
Blend dough with butter or margarine in pan.
Add 1 1/2 cups fruit on top of dough.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup sugar on top of pie.
Bake at 375° until lightly brown. Any fruit can be used with this recipe:
apple, cherry, peach, etc.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions and set aside.
Cook broccoli and set aside.
Saute onion and celery in oleo until tender.
Add broccoli, rice and other ingredients and mix.
I also add a small can of mushroom pieces extra.
Place mixture in greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Melt ingredients in double boiler; cool. Fold 1 cup of whipped cream into cooled mixture.
Pour into graham cracker crusts and chill several hours before cutting.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix together in baking dish, cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate goop cake
directions: Pour cake mix into pan.
Mix 2 eggs with butter and cake mix. Pat into pan.
Beat 2 eggs and cream cheese to powdered sugar. Pour over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown the ground beef and drain.
Add soup, Veg-All, salt and pepper.
Pour into casserole dish.
Mix Bisquick and milk together and spoon over beef mixture.
Bake at 400° until biscuits are done.

title: frog eye salad
directions: Cook acini de pepe (found at the store near the pastas).
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Let stand until it's room temperature. Drain 1 cup juice from pineapple.
Stir in flour, sugar and salt. Cook until thick and let cool.
Mix with acini de pepe and let set 1 hour (or overnight) in the refrigerator.
Mix with pineapple chunks, mandarin oranges, marshmallows and Cool Whip.
Chill and serve.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Spread sauerkraut in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread salad dressing on kraut and dot with 2 tablespoons of butter.
Sprinkle with caraway seed.
Top with corned beef and cheese.
Spread cubes on top.
Dot with remaining butter.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: red velvet pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add dry ingredients and milk.
Add food coloring and vanilla and beat.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Use cream cheese icing to frost cake.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini, carrots and onions 5 minutes and drain.
Mix margarine.
Combine soup and sour cream.
Fold in drained zucchini mixture.
Combine stuffing and margarine.

title: swiss steak
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Rub meat with garlic.
Combine flour, salt and pepper.
With a meat mallet, pound all the flour mixture into the meat.

title: hamburger or hot dog buns
directions: Mix ingredients and add enough flour to make a soft dough. Raise once, roll out to 1 1/2-inch thick and cut with tuna can. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: sugar cream cake
directions: Mix cake mix, butter or margarine and 2 eggs; spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Mix the sugar, cream cheese and 2 eggs and spread over cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Tastes like Sugar Cream Pie.

title: spicy hamburger casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add tomatoes, beans, chili powder, garlic powder and tomato sauce.
Heat until bubbles.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Tear tortillas into pieces and layer on bottom. Spoon layer of hamburger mixture.
Repeat.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crock-pot barbecue pork roast
directions: Place roast and water in crock-pot.
Cook on low for 10 hours. Remove
fat
and
bone;
slice
or tear apart.
Return roast to crock-pot.	Soak
onion
flakes
in
small amount of water. Combine remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour over meat and cook 5 hours longer.
Yields 16 to 20 servings.

title: hominy casserole(serves 8)
directions: Layer hominy and Monterey Jack cheese in large, greased baking dish.
Mix sour cream and green chilies in bowl.
Spoon over layers.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until brown and bubbly.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Remove seeds and wash peppers. Mix beef, rice, salt, pepper, egg, onion and 1/2 c. soup. Stuff peppers lightly and place in shallow pan. Top each pepper with 1 tbsp. soup. Mix remaining soup and water, pour over peppers. Bake at 350° for about 35
to 45 minutes. Serves 4.

title: broccoli and spinach casserole
directions: Bake at 350° until bread crumbs are browned.

title: ham and cauliflower casserole
directions: Separate cauliflower into flowerets.
Set aside.
Cook in boiling water to tender, not mushy.
Drain.
Cut ham into small chunks.
Set aside.
Combine in top of double boiler tapioca, butter, salt, pepper, paprika and hot milk.
Cook over boiling water, stirring frequently, until tapioca is clear (about 8 minutes).

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well and turn into an oiled 8 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake about 45 minutes in preheated 350° oven.

title: red hot salad
directions: Dissolve red hots in hot water and combine with Jell-O and applesauce.
Set aside half of mixture.
Chill remaining half until set.
Combine mayonnaise, cream cheese, celery and walnuts. Spread on chilled Jell-O and top with remaining mixture.

title: strawberry dip
directions: Soften cream cheeses.
Mix with sugar and Cool Whip.
(I serve this with strawberries; it's also good with bagels, crackers or just by itself.)

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Prepare macaroni; drain and rinse.
Heat milk in double boiler to 180°.
Melt margarine.
Add flour to make a roux.
Add to milk, stirring until dissolved.
Milk should begin to thicken. Add cheese; stir until melted entirely.
Combine elbows and cheese sauce in baking pan.
Mix margarine with bread crumbs; sprinkle over macaroni.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, until golden brown.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and water together in saucepan and cook until thickened.
Add egg yolks and salt.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and lemonade. Pour into baked pie shell and cool.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Drain pineapple and save juice.
Mix Jell-O with 2 cups hot water and use pineapple juice for cold.
Chill until thick but not solid. Add pineapple, cranberries, marshmallows and nuts.
Mix well. Fold in whipped cream.
Chill overnight.

title: twenty-four hour fruit salad
directions: Combine lemon juice, egg yolks, sugar and salt and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
When cold, add to stiff whipped cream.
Cut up fruit and add whipped cream dressing.
Let stand in refrigerator 24 hours.
Can add marshmallows and bananas before serving, if desired.
Will serve a large group.

title: pastitsio
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain and set aside.
In medium saucepan, cook lamb and onion until meat is browned; drain well.
Stir in macaroni, tomato sauce, 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese, 1/2 teaspoon salt, thyme and 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon.
Spread meat mixture in a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on cake box.
Cool and slice each layer into 2 layers.
Mix sugar, sour cream and flavoring.
Add 1 1/2 packages of coconut to the sugar mixture.
Place the filling between layers only.
Mix remaining coconut and Cool Whip; place on sides and top.
Keep refrigerated.

title: stuffed chicken breasts with mushroom sauce
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Stir hot water, 4 tablespoons of the margarine and contents of vegetable-seasoning packet in bowl until margarine is melted.
Add stuffing crumbs and egg.
Stir until moist.

title: potato casserole
directions: Wash and boil potatoes (leave at a stage you can grate).
Cool and peel.
Grate on coarse part of grater.
Place in buttered dripper pan.
Mix together sour cream, chicken soup and water, 1/2 cup cheese, onion or chives, salt and pepper.
Put on top of potatoes.
Top with crushed corn flakes and melted butter. Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy quiche
directions: Blend mayonnaise, milk, eggs and cornstarch until smooth. Stir in other ingredients.
(Try various combinations of meat and vegetables for filling.)
Bake in pastry shell for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: baklava
directions: Thaw fillo dough at room temperature for 2 hours. Finely chop or grind nuts. Cut fillo in half-crosswise. Cover with slightly damp towel. Lightly butter the bottom of 14x10x2 inch baking pan. Lay 100 of the half sheets of fillo in pan, brushing each sheet with some of the melted butter. Mix walnuts, almonds, sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, and cloves. Sprinkle half of the nut mixture over fillo in pan. Drizzle with some of the melted butter. Top with another 20 of the half sheets of fillo, brushing each with more of the melted butter. Repeat with another layer of the nut mixture, remaining butter, and remaining fill. Cut without cutting through bottom layer into diamond shaped pieces or squared. Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes. Finish cutting, cool thoroughly. Pour warm lemon-honey syrup over.
Makes about 24 diamonds.

title: vegetable surprise
directions: Cook vegetables according to package directions.
Drain.
Melt the butter and brown the Rice Krispies.
Mix remaining ingredients in a buttered casserole, placing the Rice Krispies over the top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: french apple pie
directions: Mix apples with 1/2 cup of sugar, cinnamon and lemon juice and arrange in pie shell.
Mix brown sugar and flour; cut in butter until mixture is like meal.
Add nuts and sprinkle mixture over apples.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes, then reduce heat to 375° and cook 30 minutes longer until done.

title: red snapper with dill sauce
directions: Combine mayonnaise, garlic, lemon juice, green onion, dill and ground pepper in a small bowl; set sauce aside.

title: walton's mountain coffee cake
directions: Grease a 10-inch fluted tube pan.
Sprinkle pecans in bottom of pan.
Arrange frozen dough balls on top of pecans.
Sprinkle dry pudding mix over dough balls.

In small saucepan, cook and stir brown sugar, butter and cinnamon until butter is melted. Pour butter mixture over pudding mix and dough balls in tube pan. Cover with Saran Wrap and refrigerate for 12 to 24 hours.
Uncover and bake in a 350° oven for about 30 minutes.
Immediately invert pan onto plate; let stand 15 minutes, then gently remove.

title: strawberry sour cream sauce(serve with cake, custard or fruit gelatin)
directions: Combine ingredients and spoon over cake, custard, fruit gelatin, etc.

title: burrito bites - appetizer
directions: Warm tortillas as package indicates.
Mix cream cheese, sour cream, peppers and taco seasoning together.
Spread on warm tortillas and roll up.
Refrigerate for a couple of hours, then cut into bite-size pieces.
Serve with picante sauce.

title: heavenly lite banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding mix and skim milk with vanilla extract.
Layer casserole dish with vanilla wafers, bananas and pudding mix.
Make two layers.
Cover with vanilla wafers and add Cool Whip topping.

title: applesauce walnut cake(12 to 16 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Combine cake mix, eggs, applesauce, butter and cinnamon in a large bowl. Beat at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Stir in walnuts.
Pour into pan.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes or until toothpick inserted into cake comes out clean.
Cool for 25 minutes.
Dust with confectioners sugar.

title: pig pickin cake
directions: Combine cake mix, eggs, oil and oranges.
Beat 5 minutes at high speed.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in 2 round cake pans or 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: whiskey slush
directions: Mix in container and freeze until icy.

title: squash casserole
directions: Crumble cornbread (may use 2 boxes of Jiffy mix); add melted butter.
Put half in large baking dish, 9 x 13-inch.
Combine other ingredients and pour over crust.
Add remaining crust (top), then bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: cocoa-spice snackin' cake
directions: Combine melted butter and cocoa; blend in applesauce.
Combine flour, sugar, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt in large bowl.
Blend in cocoa mixture and egg until dry ingredients are moistened.
Stir in nuts.

title: creamed carrots and bacon
directions: Peel carrots and slice thin, then cook in water until tender. Cut bacon into small pieces and brown until done.
Take out of grease.
Pour a little grease into cream sauce and stir.
Drain carrots and stir into sauce.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes and serve. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake, covered, at 350°
for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 16.

title: beef casserole
directions: Brown beef in shortening until red disappears.
Add onion, salt, pepper, mushrooms, tomato soup, parsley and sauces.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Cook macaroni; drain and add to beef mixture. Gently spoon mushroom soup into mixture.
Put in greased casserole dish and sprinkle cheese on top or put in mixture and cook for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: potato salad
directions: Toss potatoes, eggs, celery and onion.
Mix together in separate bowl sour cream, mustard, pepper, salt, salad dressing and lemon juice; blend well.
Add to potato mix and blend well together.

title: egg roll
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in egg roll shells and fry until brown.

title: freezer raspberry jam from tomatoes
directions: Place tomatoes in saucepan.
Add sugar and lemon juice; bring to boil for 20 minutes.
Turn off pan.
Stir in Jell-O; mix well. Let stand 5 minutes.
Put into small containers and put in freezer.

title: mama t's strawberry delight
directions: For crust, mix cracker crumbs with soft butter.
Press in baking dish and bake at 375° for 8 minutes and cool.
Mix cream cheese and sugar.
Blend together with Dream Whip and pour over the graham cracker crust.
Pour strawberry pie filling over all.
Chill and serve.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Remove broccoli leaves, and cut off tough ends of stalks; discard.
Wash thoroughly and cut into 1-inch pieces.
Combine broccoli, cauliflower and next 3 ingredients in a large bowl.

title: ready-bake bran muffins
directions: In a large bowl, mix bran cereal with boiling water; stir to moisten.
Set aside until cool, then add eggs, buttermilk, oil and fruit; blend well.
Stir together the dry ingredients and add. Spoon batter into greased 2 1/2-inch muffin cups, filling 2/3 full.
Bake in 425° oven about 20 minutes or until done.
Serve hot.
Makes 2 to 2 1/2 dozen muffins.

title: beef 'n' noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions, drain.
In large skillet, saute onions and pepper in butter 3 minutes.
Add beef and cook until done.
Drain excess fat.
In a medium bowl combine tomato paste and sour cream; stir in noodles and cottage cheese. Layer half the noodles and cottage cheese mixture in 2-quart casserole dish; top with half beef mixture.
Repeat.
Pour tomato sauce evenly over the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: dwayne's eggnog
directions: Beat egg whites to peaks; add sugar to them.
Beat yolks in separate bowl, add half and half to yolks.
Add yolk mixture to whites, beat together until well blended.
Add nutmeg to mixture and stir.
Sprinkle nutmeg on glass after eggnog is served. Makes about 6 servings.
Adding liquor is optional.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti.
Stir in margarine, Parmesan cheese and eggs.
Form spaghetti mixture into a crust in a buttered 10-inch pie plate.
Spread cottage cheese over crust.
Cook meat, onion and green pepper; drain.
Stir in undrained chopped tomatoes, tomato paste, oregano and garlic salt; heat.

title: pie crust (a)
directions: Mix until lard softens and add flour.
Blend well and chill before rolling out.

title: ginger crackles
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a a large bowl, combine flour, ginger, baking soda, cinnamon, cloves, and salt.
In another large bowl, beat the butter, shortening, and 1 cup of the sugar with a mixer or wooden spoon until well combined.
Add the egg and molasses to the butter mixture; beat well.
Add the dry ingredients and mix until well blended, scraping down the bowl often.
Shape the dough into 1 inch balls.
Roll each ball in the remaining sugar.
Place the balls 2 inches apart on a parchment lined baking sheet.
Bake until the cookies are lightly browned around the edges and puffed, about 13 minutes.
If you like them crispier, bake a little longer.
Let the cookies sit for 5 minutes before transferring them to a rack to cool.
Yields about 3 dozen.

title: stuffed pepper casserole
directions: Lay cut peppers in bottom of baking dish.
Mix the next 5 ingredients together.
Add 4 ounces (1/2 cup) tomato sauce and a few dashes of Texas Pete.
Mix well with meat mixture.
Lay on top of peppers.
Top with remaining tomato sauce.
Bake at 350°, covered, for about 45 minutes.
Remove cover and top with cheese. Bake until cheese melts.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add the well beaten eggs.
Add milk and vanilla.
Sift the flour and baking powder together, add a little at a time.
Form rolls with dough, about 1 1/2-inches in diameter.

title: rainbow snowball cake
directions: Chill 10-inch tube pan with removable bottom.
With small scoop, shape balls of strawberry, orange and lime.
Place on cookie sheet and freeze until firm.

title: perogi casserole
directions: Cook and mash potatoes.
Add cheese and mix until melted. Cook lasagna noodles according to package directions and cool. Melt butter and slice onion.
On bottom of a 9 x 13-inch cake pan, pour some butter and cover with some onion.
Place 3 lasagna noodles on top of onion mixture.
Spread half of potato mixture on lasagna noodles.
Continue with 3 more noodles, the rest of the potatoes and the last 3 noodles.
Top with butter and onion.
Bake until heated well in a 350° oven about 35 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken nuggets
directions: Cut chicken into 1 1/2-inch cubes.
In a bowl, stir together egg and oil.
Dip each chicken piece in egg and then in crumbs to coat.
Arrange chicken on a paper plate.
Cover with another paper plate and microwave on Medium-high for 8 minutes.

title: tahitian chicken
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces; dip in egg and then cornstarch until thoroughly coated.
Cook in oil over medium heat until hot and brown.
Remove and hold.
Drain pineapple and add enough water to syrup to make 2 cups.
To pan drippings, add pineapple syrup; stir in sugar, vinegar, soy sauce and ginger. Heat to boiling until sugar dissolves.
Stir in carrots and green pepper; reduce heat and cover.
Cook until tender-crisp, about 5 minutes.
Mix 2 tablespoons plus 3 teaspoons cornstarch and water until smooth.
Stir in egg mixture; stir constantly until thickened.
Boil 1 minute; stir in chicken, pineapple and almonds and heat slowly until hot.
Serve over rice.
Garnish with mandarin oranges and parsley.

title: dried apple slices
directions: Slice apples into desired shapes.
Dip in solution of lemon juice and salt.
Bake in oven on low (200°) for 1 to 2 hours.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Melt marshmallows in hot milk.
Stir all other ingredients into hot milk and marshmallows.
Crush cookies real fine, put in loaf pan and chill 10 to 12 hours.
I always save out a few pecans and cherries to decorate the top of the fruitcake by halving a few cherries, add a half cherry and a pecan half and keep it going until it is covered on top.
It is a good one and very easy to make.

title: dump cake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, spread cherry pie filling in bottom of pan and on top of this spread crushed pineapple.
Sprinkle dry cake mix on top of crushed pineapple and spoon butter over dry cake mix. Sprinkle coconut and nuts on butter.
Cover rack with foil. Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: sweet potato casserole(serves lots)
directions: Peel, slice and cook sweet potatoes.
Drain.
Add margarine. Mash; sweeten to taste.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Put in casserole dish.

title: freezing strawberries
directions: Combine sugar and mashed berries; let set while cooking Sure-Jell and water for 1 minute.
Add sugar mixture; pour over whole berries in containers and freeze.
This keeps the berries firm when thawed.

title: eclair cake
directions: Heat water and margarine to boiling.
Add flour and eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg is added.
Spread in a well greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then poke with fork at 1 inch intervals.
Bake for another 15 minutes (total of 30 minutes).
Cool completely.

title: hot dip
directions: Brown sausage, hamburger and onion in pan.
Add garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Stir in chiles and cubed cheese; heat until cheese melts.
Serve with chips or crackers.
Serve warm.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Beat sour cream with cream cheese until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice, onion, pepper, milk and shrimp (save a few shrimp for a garnish).
Season with salt or Worcestershire sauce.
Cover and chill at least 2 hours.
(Can be made a day ahead.)

title: armadillo eggs
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients at room temperature well.
Stuff each pepper half and roll stuffed peppers in remaining mixture to completely enclose pepper.
Place on baking sheet and bake at 375° for 15 minutes, turning halfway for even browning.
Yield: approximately 24 to 30 "eggs" depending on size of eggs.

title: homemade biscuits
directions: Sift flour; cut in shortening with fork until crumbly.
Mix in milk until very moist.
Knead only enough to form small rolls. Roll in palm of hand and press.
Will make perfect circles.
Grease bottom of pan well.
Preheat oven to 450°.
Bake until lightly browned on bottom, then broil until golden brown on top.
Makes 12 to 15 biscuits.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating after each egg.
Sift flour, salt and soda together.
Add flour mixture and sour cream alternately.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Bake in Bundt pan.

title: eggs in blanket(appetizers)
directions: Wrap each hard-boiled egg in sausage, then roll in Shake 'n Bake.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Chill. Cut into quarters.

title: southern sweet potato pie
directions: Boil sweet potatoes until done; remove skin and mash until all lumps are dissolved.
Add sugar and margarine or butter.
Continue beating; add milk, nutmeg, vanilla and eggs and beat until smooth. Pour in 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 425° until done, about 35 minutes.

title: better than sex chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Prepare and bake cake mix as directed on package.
When cake is still warm, but not hot, poke holes in cake about 1 inch apart with handle of wooden spoon.
Pour sweetened condensed milk over cake, then pour butterscotch caramel fudge over cake.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Top with Cool Whip and crushed candy bars.
Keep refrigerated.

title: raisin-nut sandwich filling
directions: Beat egg.
Add sugar, lemon juice and lemon rind.
Cook until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add raisins and nuts.
Add pinch of salt.
Mix well.
When cool, add 1 cup mayonnaise.
Mix well. Place in covered container.
Keep in refrigerator.
Delicious on brown bread.

title: frozen pudding bars(makes 6 pudding pops.)
directions: Prepare pudding mix with milk as directed on package. Pour into pop molds or paper or plastic cups. Insert wooden stick or spoon into each cup. Freeze until firm, about 5 hours.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown garlic in olive oil and remove.
Brown sausage and beef. Add green pepper, tomato sauce, tomato paste and seasonings. Simmer 3 hours.
Add oregano last hour.

title: easy fudge bars
directions: Cook pudding in large saucepan as directed on package.
Stir dry cake mix into hot pudding.
Beat 2 minutes on medium speed. Pour batter into greased and floured jelly roll pan.
Sprinkle with chips and nuts.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: carole's good pie crust*
directions: *Excellent for fried pies.

title: salad dressing
directions: Heat vinegar and sugar together, mixing well.
Combine all ingredients.
Store in refrigerator.

title: suttons bay chili
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Boil a few minutes, then simmer.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, margarine and 4 tablespoons sugar.
Put into a long 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 6 or 7 minutes. Let cool.
Mix cream cheese and 1 cup sugar.
Fold Cool Whip into cream cheese mixture.
Spread over pretzels.
Layer.
Prepare Jell-O according to directions and add strawberries; pour on top of the cheese layer when Jell-O has slightly thickened. Refrigerate.
Serve cold.

title: hog dog bean skillet dish
directions: Cook and stir bacon and onion in 10-inch skillet until bacon is brown; drain.
Stir in macaroni, sauce mix, water, pork and beans, frankfurters and mustard.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer, stirring occasionally, until macaroni is tender, about 15 minutes.
Uncover and cook until desired consistency.
Makes 6 servings.

title: peanut butter blossom cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and peanut butter.
Add 1/2 cup of sugar and brown sugar; beat until fluffy.
Beat in egg, vanilla and milk until blended.
Gradually add flour, salt and baking soda.
Shape in balls and roll in remaining 1/4 cup sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.
Remove from oven and immediately press Kiss in each cookie so it cracks around the edges.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute broccoli, onion and celery in the margarine for 15 minutes.
Cook rice as directed on box.
Add soup, milk and cheese to broccoli mixture and add the cooked rice to mixture, also.
Put into a greased dish, approximately 10 x 10-inch.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.
Can make ahead and freeze, then bake when ready to serve.

title: sealegs crostini
directions: Preheat the broiler.
Line a broiler pan with foil.
In a medium bowl, combine the sealegs, bell pepper, mayonnaise, parsley, chives, lime juice, mustard, Parmesan cheese and hot pepper sauce and blend well.
Spread 1 tablespoon of mixture on each slice of bread.
Place the crostini on the broiler pan and broil 4 inches from the heat for 5 to 6 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: azalie's pickles
directions: Replace dill chips to jar.
Pour ingredients from bowl over dill chips.
Shake well.
Add pickle juice to completely fill jar. Shake well.
Refrigerate.

title: cream cheese salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add fruit juice; chill until partially set.
With a mixer, blend cream cheese into gelatin. Whip the cream; add to gelatin.
Mix in fruit, nuts and marshmallows.
Put in molds or 8-inch square pan.
Chill until firm.
Serves 9.

title: mock sangria
directions: Combine juices.
Just before serving, add club soda.
Stir and garnish.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat until fluffy.
Add vanilla, baking powder and milk.
Mix well.
Stir in cracker crumbs, coconut and walnuts.
Pour into Bundt or tube pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: seafood salad
directions: Mix together and chill.
Better if it sits overnight.

title: apple dumplings
directions: For syrup, mix first 4 ingredients, bring to boiling.
Remove from heat; add butter.

title: chocolate cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix warm water and yeast.
Add the remaining ingredients and mix well.
Let rise for 1 hour.
Knead slightly and roll into a rectangle.
Spread with soft butter.
Sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar mix.
Roll dough and slice off rolls about 1/2-inch thick.
Place on buttered pan and let rise again until double.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Glaze with powdered sugar and milk mixture.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix sugar, milk and margarine and bring to a boil.
Let boil slowly for
10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Cut off and put other ingredients
in.
Pour into greased 8 or 9-inch pan. Add 1 cup pecans, if desired.

title: lemon pound cake with icing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Blend at low speed of mixer just to moisten, then beat 3 minutes at medium speed.

title: tuna and pea salad in shells
directions: Cook peas as directed on package; drain and cool.
Cook macaroni as directed on package; drain.
Set aside in bowl of cold water.
In large bowl, combine remaining ingredients, except lettuce.
Add peas; toss gently.
Drain water from cooked macaroni.
Line each macaroni shell with lettuce leaf.
Spoon about 1/4 cup tuna mixture into each shell.
Place in shallow dish.
Cover and refrigerate until thoroughly chilled.
To serve, place shells on individual serving plates.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: heavenly salad
directions: Mix jello with 1/2 cup hot water and 1/2 cup cold water. Dissolve completely.
Let jello set until slightly firm.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Stir in jello.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: cherry angel food cake
directions: Mix according to directions on box, except use juice from cherries for part of the water. Chop cherries and fold in last. Bake according to directions on box.

title: carolyn's pecans
directions: Put all into a jar and shake.
Put onto a cookie sheet and bake for 1 hour at 225°. Remove and toss with 1 Tbsp.
melted butter.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt.
Bake again for 20 minutes.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Combine cream cheese, pineapple, green pepper, onion and salt; mix well.
Chill.
Shape into a 4-inch ball and roll in pecans. Yields about 2 1/2 cups.

title: chili soup
directions: Saute onion and green pepper.
Brown ground beef; add salt and pepper.
Add this to the tomato soup and water.
While this is simmering dice the potatoes and add to the mixture.
Add chili powder.
Cook slowly until potatoes are done.
Canned kidney beans can be added if desired.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix corn meal, egg and milk together; add creamed corn. Grease bottom of casserole dish; pour half of corn meal batter into dish.
Layer meat, peppers, onion and cheese on top of corn meal mix in casserole dish.
Top with remaining corn meal mix and bake at 375° for 1 hour, or until brown.

title: chocolate peanut butter bars
directions: Beat peanut butter or butter until smooth; add sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Blend in flour and salt.
Stir in 1 cup chocolate morsels.
Spread in an ungreased jelly roll pan.

title: self-filled cupcakes
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions.
Spoon batter into paper-filled muffin pan; fill 2/3 full.
Combine cream cheese and sugar; cream until light and fluffy.
Add egg and salt; beat well. Stir in chocolate morsels.
Spoon 1 heaping teaspoon of cream cheese mixture into center of each cupcake.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen cupcakes.

title: dump cake
directions: Can use blueberry or cherry pie filling.

title: seafood loaf
directions: Drain salmon, reserving 1/4 cup liquid.
Remove skin and bones from salmon; flake.
Thoroughly mix salmon liquid and remaining ingredients.
Pack into a well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until browned.
Cool loaf in pan for 10 minutes; loosen from sides of pan and turn out on serving platter.
Garnish with parsley, lemon and orange slices.

title: creamed tacos
directions: Saute onion, chopped, in large skillet. Add all ingredients. Cook until it bubbles. Place taco-flavored Doritos in pan. Pour sauce over them, another layer of chips and remainder of chips and sauce. Cover with cheese. Place in oven at 350° until cheese melts.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Reserve one cup of almond cream for later.
Cut cake lengthwise in half, then crosshalf.
Prepare vanilla with 1 1/2 cups milk and almond; fold in 2 cups Cool Whip.
Drain syrup from one package of strawberries, add orange juice and spread 1 cup almond cream.
Arrange half of pound cake slices over almond cream.
Drizzle half of orange juice mixture over cake to moisten it.
Top cake with half of strawberries, spread almond cream on top.
Moisten cake with remaining juice mixture; add peaches. Arrange remaining strawberries in circle, spoon reserved cream in middle and sprinkle with almonds.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Cream the sugar, butter, egg, melted chocolate square or cocoa and milk.
Mix baking soda with flour.
Add dry to creamed ingredients.
Blend, then add vanilla.
Grease and flour a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: sweet potato puffs
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, butter, bourbon and salt; mix well. Combine pecans and brown sugar in a small bowl.
Pat 2 generous tablespoons of sweet potato mixture around each marshmallow.
Roll each in nuts and sugar.

title: shoyu chicken
directions: In large pot, enough to cover whole chicken, fry ginger in oil until golden brown.
In small bowl,
mix
shoyu,
sugar and anise. Add to oil; allow to boil.
Add chicken and cover. Cook 10 minutes on	back,
then
turn
and	cook 10 minutes on breast. Remove from pot, chop and serve.

title: strawberry surprise
directions: In a large bowl, mix jello and pineapple.
Add cottage cheese, Cool Whip, coconut and marshmallows.
Stir well and refrigerate before serving.

title: lemon pie filling
directions: Blend cornstarch, sugar and
salt
in
a saucepan.
Add water. Heat rapidly and when thick add well beaten egg yolks. Cook 15 minutes; watch and stir.
Blend in butter, lemon juice and rind. Pour into 9-inch
baked
pie
shell
and cover with meringue made from the
three
egg whites.
Bake eight minutes at 400°.

title: savory rice with lobster
directions: Cook lobster in boiling water 6 minutes after water returns to boil.
Drain, rinse and cube.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Brown lightly in melted butter.
Don't let it toughen and dry out. Combine oil and lemon seasonings; mix well.
Add wine.
Add to cooked rice.
Heat over medium heat 2 to 3 minutes, stirring gently.
Add cubed lobster and mix well.
Serves 4.

title: low calorie dip for veggies
directions: Put all ingredients into a blender and mix well.
Chill.
If the dip seems a little too thick, add a little skim milk gradually and mix again until you get the consistency you want.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Dump pineapple with juice into pan; spread evenly over bottom. Pour coconut over fruit; spread dry cake mix over pineapple. Spread entire surface with thin slices of butter. Do not mix. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes. Top should be lightly brown.

title: old-fashioned tomato spice cake
directions: Sift first 7 ingredients together into bowl.
Dissolve baking soda in tomato sauce. Add tomato sauce, egg, oil, nuts and raisins and mix well.
Pour into 2 greased 8-inch layer cake pans or Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and frost with a lemon-butter icing or a cream cheese frosting.

title: hot and spicy tex-mex muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Lightly grease 12 muffin cups. Combine all ingredients except cornmeal mix. Add cornmeal mix and blend well. Fill muffin cups 2/4 to almost full. Bake 18 to 20 minutes or until browned.
tags: White Lilly Self-rising Buttermilk Cornmeal Mix

title: dried beef ball
directions: Chop dried beef and divide in half.
Chop scallion tops fine. Mix dried beef (2 ounces), cream cheese (softened), scallion tops and garlic powder with a spoon.
Take a piece of wax paper, spread remaining dried beef.
Mold mixture into a ball and roll in the dried beef.
Serve with crackers.

title: tiger surprises
directions: Spread peanut butter between two Ritz crackers.
Melt white chocolate with paraffin in double boiler.
Dip each cracker in chocolate and cool on wax paper.

title: reese's cups
directions: Line muffin pans with cupcake liners.
Melt chocolate bar. Add 1/2 cup peanut butter.
Melt 1 cup peanut butter.
Layer in muffin liners as follows:
chocolate layer and let set; peanut butter layer and let set; and chocolate layer and let set.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: May add nuts, if wanted.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles in salt until semi-tender.
Brown meat; add garlic and onion.
Cook until onion is tender.
Add seasonings, tomato sauce and paste.
Cover and simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Mix cottage cheese, cream cheese and egg with a mixer.
Layer as follows: 3 noodles, 1/3 meat sauce, noodles, 1/2 cheese mix, 1/2 Mozzarella cheese, noodles, 1/3 meat sauce, 1/2 cheese mix, 1/2 Mozzarella cheese, 1/3 sauce and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let cool about 15 minutes before serving.

title: lemon supreme cake
directions: Mix cake mix, nectar, oil and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time. Bake in tube pan (greased and floured) at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool right side up for 15 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Glaze.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Place chicken and water in a Dutch oven. Cover and bring to a boil. Reduce heat to simmer; cook until chicken is tender, about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: melt in your mouth cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl and blend well.
Pour into an 8-inch pan or iron skillet.
Grease well.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: pineapple-nut dip
directions: Cook pineapple and sugar until thick; then cool.
Mix other ingredients together with pineapple.
Refrigerate.
Cut fresh pineapple in half lengthwise.
Cut out pineapple and fill with dip.
Serve with Town House crackers.

title: jollof rice(west africa)
directions: Boil
the cubed meats about 1/2 hour. Remove from broth and drain. Brown in cooking oil. Remove from oil. Slice onions and tomatoes
and cook in the oil. Add 1 can tomato puree. Add black and red peppers and
thyme.
Add meats to this sauce and simmer for 1/2 hour. Cook rice, salt and liquid as directed on package, watching that it
does
not
scorch.
Cook	the peas. After rice is cooked, gently
fold
the
sauce and cooked peas into
it and serve
while
hot.	(Cooked
green	beans,	green peppers or even French fried
potatoes
can be used instead of the peas.)

title: fried fish
directions: Combine cornmeal,
salt,
pepper
and cayenne pepper in small mixing bowl.
Spread
onto	a
sheet
of
aluminum foil. Dredge fish in cornmeal mix.
Heat shortening in large frypan. Fry fish until golden
brown
and
flaky, about 4 minutes each side. Remove from pan; drain on paper towels.
Serve hot with lemon wedge or juice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pizza muffins
directions: Split the English muffin in half.
Spread pizza sauce all over inside layer of muffins.
Put Mozzarella cheese over the pizza sauce.
Put the toppings you picked on the muffin.
Put muffin in microwave for 1 minute.

title: cheese cake bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place one package crescent rolls in greased 9 x 13-inch dark glass or non-stick pan.
Gently press seams together to make one flat base.
Mix cream cheese, sugar, egg yolk and vanilla together well.
Spread over base.
Unfold second can of crescent rolls and place over the mixture.
Gently press seams together.

title: layered pudding cake
directions: Need a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: banana split cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Crumble graham crackers.
Mix in melted butter.
Spread mixture onto bottom of 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan. Bake for 6 to 8 minutes.
Cool.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Thoroughly mix with hands until mass holds shape.
Form into balls and bake on lightly greased cookie sheet at 400° for 10 minutes.
Make ahead and freeze to cook later.
Make 5 to 6 dozen walnut-sized balls.

title: german chocolate bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine cake mix, 1/3 cup evaporated milk and margarine.
Mix well.
Pat 2/3 of mixture into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 6 minutes.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts over warm bottom.
Melt caramels with 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Stir until blended.
Pour caramel mixture over chips and nuts.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/3 of cake mixture.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool; cut into bars.

title: old-fashioned beef stew
directions: Coat meat with flour; set excess flour aside.
In a large skillet, heat oil.
Brown meat on all sides.
In a slow cooking pot, combine browned beef, bay leaf, Worcestershire sauce, chopped onions, bouillon, pepper, salt, sugar and vegetables.
Pour water over all.
Cover and cook on low for 8 to 10 hours.
Turn control on high.
Thicken with flour leftover from coating, about 1/4 cup, dissolved in a small amount of water.
Cover and cook on high for 10 to 15 minutes or until slightly thickened.

title: venison roast
directions: Combine roast, water to cover and 1/4 cup salt in a large Dutch oven.
Cover and let soak 2 hours.
Drain, rinse and pat dry. Combine seasoned salt, garlic powder and pepper; sprinkle on both sides of roast.
Sprinkle with soy sauce.
Place onion slices on top of roast; sprinkle with 2 tablespoons of flour.
Place pats of butter on onion.
Wrap roast twice in heavy-duty aluminum foil. Place in roasting pan.
Add 1 quart water.
Cover and bake at 350° for 4 to 5 hours.
Add water, if necessary, to roasting pan, but do not open foil.

title: baked lemon pudding cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Beat egg whites in small mixer bowl at high speed until foamy (1 to 2 minutes). Continue beating, gradually adding 1/4 cup sugar, until glossy and stiff peaks form (2 to 3 minutes). Set aside.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add sauce and spices.
Butter both sides of shells.
In greased casserole, put in layers the shells, meat sauce, cheese and olives.
Repeat to top of pan, ending with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Separate
eggs.
Beat egg yolks, sugar and spices until smooth.
Add
pumpkin.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold into pumpkin mixture.
Bake for 15 minutes at 425°.
Reduce temperature to 350° and continue to bake for 30 minutes.

title: english toffee
directions: Melt butter under low fire.
Add sugar and water; boil to 300°.
Remove and pour into buttered pans.
When cold, spread with warm melted chocolate and sprinkle with nuts.

title: zucchini indian relish
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Add to kettle.
Stirring, bring to boil and cook 10 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Put in sterilized jars and seal.

title: strawberry pleasure
directions: Put crumbs in oblong dish and pour butter over.
Mix well and press into dish.
Beat cream cheese until soft and stir in milk to blend.
Mix in lemon juice and spread over crumbs.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in berries and pour over cream cheese mixture.
Chill until firm.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to a boil, then add to combined dry ingredients.
Beat well and add eggs.
Continue beating and fold in sour cream.
Pour into greased cookie sheet pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: hominy
directions: Mix and warm in oven at 200°.

title: blueberry torte
directions: Mix and pat into 8 x 12-inch pan 1/2 cup melted margarine, crumbs and 1/2 cup granulated sugar.
Whip together cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar and eggs.
Spread mixture over crumbs.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Spread blueberries over top and top with whipped cream.

title: custard pie(heritage recipe)
directions: Preheat oven to 475 degrees.
Mix thoroughly eggs, sugar, salt, and vanilla.
Slowly stir in hot milk.
Pour at once into unbaked shell.
Dash top with nutmeg.
Bake in hot oven at 475 degrees for 5 minutes,
and reduce heat to 425 degrees and bake for 10 minutes longer or until knife comes out clean.

title: chicken or turkey tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti in chicken broth; cut pepper, onion and mushrooms and add to spaghetti and chicken.

title: communion bread
directions: Cut butter into flour and salt mixed together.
Add whipping cream, half and half and milk.
Divide dough into thirds.
Knead for 15 to 20 minutes.
Divide each third of dough in half.
Roll out on cookie sheet.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes in 375° oven until lightly brown, just on edges.

title: tacos in pasta shells
directions: Cook shells; drain.
Rinse in warm water and toss with butter. Grease 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Cook beef and drain thoroughly. Add cream cheese and 1/2 package of taco seasoning mix.
Simmer. Fill shells with meat mixture.
Place shells in baking dish and pour taco sauce over them.
Cover with foil and bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Uncover and sprinkle top with shredded cheese and crushed tortilla chips.
Bake 15 minutes more.
Remove from oven and serve.
Garnish with sour cream and favorite taco toppings.

title: shrimp gumbo express
directions: Shell and devein shrimp (frozen uncooked may be used).
Mix all ingredients, except shrimp and hot sauce.
Cover and cook 3 minutes.
Add shrimp and hot sauce; cover and simmer 5 minutes. Thicken liquid with 1 tablespoon of flour, dissolved in a little water if necessary.
Stir and cook a few minutes, until thick. Serve gumbo over hot, cooked rice in bowls.

title: king ranch chicken casserole(good!!!)
directions: Make a sauce of the soups, tomatoes and chicken broth.
Tear tortillas into 1/4's.
Into one large 3-quart casserole or 2 smaller, put a layer of tortillas, chicken, onion and cheese.
Top with about 1/4 of sauce.
Repeat until all ingredients are used, ending with layer of cheese.
Cook, covered, for 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove cover and bake for 30 minutes longer.
This casserole freezes well.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all ingredients at once.
Beat 4 minutes.
Bake in greased Bundt pan or regular sheet cake pan at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Can be glazed, dusted with xxx sugar or left plain.

title: baked cheese grits
directions: Bring 2 2/3 cups water to a boil; add grits and cook, stirring often for 5 minutes or until thickened. Remove from heat; add margarine, eggs, cheese, salt and pepper. Stir until well blended. Spoon into a 2-quart baking dish coated with cooking spray. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: taco skillet burgers
directions: In a bowl, combine the egg, milk, bread crumbs, onion and taco seasoning mix.
Add beef; mix well.
Shape mixture into 6 patties. In large lightly greased skillet, brown the patties on both sides.
Mix soup and 1/2 cup water; spoon over meat.
Cover; cook over low heat 15 minutes.
Top with tomatoes and cheese.
Heat, covered, 3 minutes longer.
Serve with corn chips.
Serves 6.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream together sugar, oil and margarine.
Add eggs and beat well.
Mix cocoa and food coloring; mix all together.
Add vinegar and buttermilk, flour and vanilla.
Beat well for 2 minutes on high.
Grease and flour 3 round cake pans.
Evenly distribute into cake pan.
Cook at 325° until done, 25 to 32 minutes.

title: chicken with chipped beef
directions: Saute whole chicken breasts in melted butter, garlic, salt and pepper.
Put in baking dish and sprinkle with lemon juice. Defrost creamed chipped beef.
Pour over chicken and add raw mushrooms.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Serve with spinach pasta.
This recipe may be fixed ahead of time and covered and left in refrigerator until ready to cook.

title: strawberry angel delight
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water; add frozen strawberries. Stir until thawed. Chill until almost set. Mix jello and Cool Whip. Pour over bite size pieces of angel food cake in 9 x 13 pan.

title: carrot salad
directions: Mix and pour over carrots and let stand overnight.

title: mom's chicken cacciatore
directions: Brown onion in oil.
Roll chicken in flour.
Remove onions, then brown chicken.
Put in casserole dish. Add salt, pepper, water, soup and desired amount of mushrooms.
Simmer approximately 1 hour or until done.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Spoon into prepared pie crust. Cover with top crust.
Crimp edges to seal.
Slit top crust and brush with egg.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and celery; drain.
Add tomatoes and puree.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Boil spaghetti and drain.
Use same pan to melt butter.
Add Parmesan cheese and beaten eggs and spaghetti to make crust.
Put spaghetti mixture in a 9 x 12-inch greased pan.
Then add cottage cheese layer.
Put meat mixture on top of cottage cheese layer.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Put grated Mozzarella on top and bake another 5 minutes.

title: cincinnati chili
directions: Boil meat in quart of water slowly until redness leaves.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil and then simmer for 3 to 4 hours.
Remove bay leaves when done.
If desired, add cracker meal to thicken.
Serve plain, with cheese or over a bed of spaghetti, topped with Colby Longhorn cheese.

title: jon's favorite casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain.
In skillet, combine hamburger, onion, diced tomatoes, oregano, garlic, sugar and jar of Ragu.
Cook elbows according to package directions.
Drain. Add elbows to skillet; simmer on low until hot.
Add favorite cheese on top if you wish.

title: steak bake
directions: Flour meat; brown on both sides in cooking oil in frying pan. Place in baking pan; cover with onion and green pepper.
Add garlic powder, salt and pepper; pour cream of mushroom soup over. Rinse can with 1/2 can of water; pour over.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Serve over rice.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Combine all ingredients and roll in small balls.
Dip in sugar and do not flatten.
Bake in a 350° oven.

title: apple pie slices
directions: Mix flour, Crisco and salt until crumbly, then add egg, vinegar and milk.
Divide dough in half.
Make 1 crust to fit 15 x 10-inch brownie pan.
Let sides extend over edges of pan to seal top of crust.

title: easy macaroons
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly by hand.
Drop by teaspoon onto well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: coconut pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour in bowl.
Beat egg yolks in bowl. Heat milk and add dry ingredients and egg yolks.
Cook until it is thickened, stirring constantly.
Add coconut and pour into shell. Make meringue by beating egg whites and cream of tartar until stiff adding sugar gradually.
Spread on pie and brown.

title: party chicken
directions: *I usually allow 2 halves per male and 1 half for females.

title: chinese rice
directions: *You can substitute chicken breasts, cut in small pieces and cook in wok at medium high heat in 4 tablespoons of oil until done, usually 10 to 15 minutes.

title: red astoria cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs; make a paste of coloring and cocoa; add to creamed mixture.
Sift flour and salt and with buttermilk, add to creamed mixture.
Stir in vinegar and soda by hand.
Bake in two 8-inch greased and floured pans at 350°.
Cool before frosting.

title: diet dip
directions: Combine onion, salt and cheese.
Beat well with mixer; chill several hours.
Stir in pimento and parsley.
Serve with celery, carrots, green pepper strips or any of your favorite raw vegetables.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: chicken divan
directions: Arrange broccoli in 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch baking pan. Place chicken on broccoli.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, curry powder, lemon juice and cheese.
Pour over chicken.
Combine bread cubes and margarine.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: english toffee
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a heavy pan.
Using a candy thermometer, cook to 300° (hard crack) on medium heat.
STIR CONSTANTLY.
Add vanilla.
Pour on to greased cookie sheet, spreading 1/4 inch thick.
Quickly lay candy bars on top . Spread evenly as they melt.
Cool, break into small pieces and wrap each in plastic wrap.
A 25 year favorite of our family!!

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 3 loaves.

title: rainbow layered jello
directions: First Layer:
Add 3/4 cup boiling water to 1 package jello. Stir until dissolved.
Add 3/4 cup cold water.
Pour into oiled 9 x 13-inch pan (Tupperware cake carrier works very well).
Chill until set.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Combine oleo, brown sugar and pretzels.
Mix well and put into slightly buttered dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Dissolve jello in boiling water.
While hot, add to chilled strawberries. Cool until mixture begins to set.
Meanwhile, cream sugar and cream cheese.
Spread over crust.
Pour jello over top and chill to set.

title: pound cake
directions: Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sour cream slaw
directions: Mix sour cream, coconut, pineapple and marshmallows.
Chill overnight.
Add cabbage and carrots.

title: homemade "shake and bake"
directions: Use as seasoned coating to bake chicken, fish or pork chops.

title: potato soup
directions: Cube potatoes; boil with onion until creamy.
Add soup and simmer about 10 minutes.

title: vegetable curried rice(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Saute onions and asparagus in oil in a large pot.
Add all vegetables, except snow peas.
Add all spices, including pepper and stir well.
Separately brown egg noodles in butter or margarine in small pan.
Add noodles, rice, broth or water to vegetables; stir well and bring to a boil.
Lower heat to low.
Cover and cook 15 minutes.
Add snow peas.
Cook another 5 minutes or until all water is absorbed.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix eggs, oil (or applesauce), sour cream and cake mix well and pour 1/2 batter in 9 x 13 pan.
Take cinnamon and mix with brown sugar.
Sprinkle on batter.
Then pour rest of batter in pan.
Cook at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool 30 minutes.
Mix 1 cup powdered sugar and 1/4 cup milk.
Punch holes in cake and pour on.
You're ready.
Enjoy the cake.

title: french onion soup
directions: Saute onions in margarine until golden.
Add water, bouillon and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Dip into bowls, cover with shredded Mozzarella cheese and place under broiler until cheese bubbles.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Finely crush crackers.
Mix raisins, pecans, coconut and chopped cherries with cracker crumbs.
In large bowl, combine marshmallows, jelly, cherry juice and milk.
Melt in microwave oven.

title: beef jerky
directions: Slice London Broil in 1/4-inch strips.
Place in liquid smoke and marinate overnight in refrigerator.
The following day place in food dehydrator and dry until done.
When cool, place in Ziploc bags and enjoy.

title: chili con carne(as gwen makes it)
directions: Brown 3 pounds lean ground beef and drain off grease.
Add onion and cook until transparent.
Salt and pepper to taste. Place in large pan and add red kidney beans and canned tomatoes. Add paprika and chili powder.
Bring to a boil and simmer for about 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Keeps well.
Also, you may freeze for another time.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix all together and bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients except bacon in a large mixing bowl until blended well.
Place in ungreased baking dish.
Place bacon strips on top and place in a 350° oven for 60 minutes.

title: karen's swiss steak
directions: Have meat put through cuber at meat department once.
Cut into serving pieces.
Dip in flour and brown in vegetable oil; salt and pepper if desired.
Remove meat from frying pan and put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Prepare packet of au jus according to directions and add to drippings in frying pan.
To this add soups, water and milk. Heat through and mix well.
Pour over meat.
Cover tightly and bake at 325° for 2 hours or until meat is very tender.
If using 2 pieces of meat, you may need larger pan and extra water or milk.

title: twenty-four hour salad
directions: Cook pudding; let cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Before serving, add 4 to 5 bananas (sliced).

title: simple salad
directions: Mix well and chill 1 hour before serving.

title: crumbled hamburger
directions: Brown onion in fat; add meat and brown.
Mix in remaining ingredients except buns.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Serve hot on toasted split buns.
Makes 8 servings.

title: 24-carat carrots
directions: Saute carrots in butter or margarine and olive oil until slightly browned.
Add milk. Blend in soup mix and flour.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes or until thickened. Cover and bake in 350° oven until tender, about 40 to 50 minutes. Tastes even better warmed up!

title: orange roughy
directions: Salt fish with Cajun Creole powder and cook together in covered skillet.
Cook 15 minutes.
Put picante sauce on top before serving.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients; bring to boil. Boil 3 minutes. Add remaining ingredients and drop on wax paper by teaspoonfuls.

title: great sugar cookies
directions: Cream eggs, sugar and butter.
Add vanilla and dry ingredients.
Start folding in flour until you use 5 cups of flour or until it rolls well.
Put in refrigerator overnight and roll to 1/4-inch thick and cut.
Sprinkle with a little sugar.
Bake at 350°.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix everything together except cheese.
Pour 1/2 mixture in baking pan, and then sprinkle cheese over this.
Add remaining mixture over cheese and bake at 400° for 1/2 hour.

title: jam bars
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Using 1 cup to 1 1/2 cups of mixture, spread onto bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Spread about 2 cups strawberry or any other flavor preserves on top of bottom layer. With the rest of mixture, crumble onto top of preserves.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: three corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix butter, sour cream and egg.
Stir in both cans of corn.
Blend in muffin mix. Pour into a well-greased casserole dish.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour until puffed, golden brown and crispy on top.

title: baked chicken
directions: Use as many pounds of chicken meat, white or dark, as desired. If low-fat desired, remove skin.
Brush with mayonnaise (can be lite).
Roll in Italian bread crumbs; if desired, sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Very good and moist.
Bake at 425° for about 45 minutes to 1 hour, until brown, skin side up.
Needs no turning.

title: zucchini hot dish
directions: Roll the zucchini in flour and fry in cooking oil.
Salt while frying.
Put zucchini in casserole after browned.
Pour tomatoes, onion and bacon over zucchini and let it heat through and become bubbly.
If you'd like, sprinkle cheese over top.

title: biscotti
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Add extract.
Gradually add flour, and baking powder.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut, turn on side and bake until light golden brown.

title: corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease a 1-quart casserole.
Melt butter or margarine in saucepan and blend in flour.
Add milk, salt, pepper and sugar.
Bring to boiling point, stirring constantly.
Blend eggs into warm mixture.
Pour into casserole. Place casserole into oven and bake 1 hour or until set.
Pudding is done when the end of a table knife inserted in the center comes out clean.
Makes six servings.

title: vidalia onion pie
directions: Cook onions in butter until clear and soft (about 15 minutes), stirring often.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix and pour into the 2 baked pie shells.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Bake in a 375° oven for 20 minutes, then lower temperature to 350° for an additional 40 minutes until lightly browned on top.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: stuffed shrimp
directions: Mix all but bread with margarine and oil until onion is soft, not brown. Fold in bread until moist. Stuff shrimp and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Baste with lemon butter sauce. Delicious!

title: monte cristo
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine eggs and milk for each sandwich.
Alternate cheese and meat between bread slices.
Dip each sandwich in egg mixture.
Brown on both sides in butter flavored Crisco.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with sugar.

title: chicken stroganoff
directions: Slice chicken into strips.
In skillet in 1 tablespoon hot butter, cook half chicken until brown.
Remove.
Cook rest of chicken until brown.
Stir often.

title: tuna seashell casserole
directions: In saucepan, melt 2 tablespoons margarine over medium heat. Add celery and onion.
Cook, stirring, for 3 minutes.
Stir in soup, milk and pimento until blended.
In a 2-quart casserole, toss macaroni and tuna.
Pour sauce over macaroni mixture.
Mix bread crumbs and the melted margarine; sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Makes 6 servings.

title: grandma's vanilla ice cream
directions: In double boiler, scald milk.
Mix sugar, flour and salt; stir in enough milk to make smooth paste.
Stir into rest of milk in double boiler.
Stir until thickened.
Cover; cook 10 minutes. Beat eggs slightly; stir in milk mixture.
Return to double boiler; cook 1 minute.
Cool.
Add vanilla and cream.
Freeze in 2-quart crank freezer until difficult to turn, using 8 parts crushed ice to 1 part ice cream salt.
Makes 1 1/4 quarts.

title: easy chocolate milk shake
directions: Put in blender 3/4 cup milk, 1/4 cup chocolate-flavored syrup and 3 large scoops vanilla ice cream. Cover and blend on low speed about 10 seconds or until smooth.
Pour into glasses and serve immediately.

title: nanny girl's eggplant pie
directions: Brown chuck in large heavy saucepan; pour out drippings.
In another pan, heat butter and oil.
Add onion and garlic; cook until transparent.
Add eggplant and bell pepper; cook, stirring occasionally until tender.
Reduce heat.
Stir in mushrooms and tomatoes; stir-fry for several minutes.
Stir in chuck, basil, salt and pepper; cook down.
For each pie shell, sprinkle 1/2 cup cheese on bottom.
Spread half of beef-eggplant mixture over cheese.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Spread hamburger on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex baking dish. In separate bowl, combine cream soups, then pour evenly over hamburger.
Drain corn; spread over soup mixture.
Next layer, add cheese.
Finally, top with Tater Tots.
Bake in a 400° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: shoo-fly cake
directions: Mix
flour,
brown
sugar
and	shortening into crumbs; save 1
cup
for
top.
Put soda in boiling water and mix all together. Grease
and
flour
9 x 13-inch pan.
Put batter in and
top with 1 cup crumbs you save from first 3 ingredients. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Place everything in a large bowl and mix together.
Then place in refrigerator overnight.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti.
Add ingredients.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Add tomatoes when ready to serve.

title: scramble
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large pan and bake in oven at 250° for 2 hours, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: clam dip
directions: Rub a mixing bowl with the garlic.
Add remaining ingredients. Blend together and place in center of a large tray and surround with potato chips, crackers or raw cauliflower buds.

title: butterscotch squares
directions: Combine dry ingredients; add margarine and vanilla.
Blend and spread in greased pan and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes; cut in squares while warm and loosen edges.
Cool thoroughly and serve.

title: date cream pie
directions: Note:
Very good in a graham cracker crust.

title: cherry delight
directions: Tear cake into large bite size pieces.
Mix pudding and pour over cake pieces.
Pour on whipping cream and top with cherry pie filling.
Cool before serving.
Use 9 x 13-inch cake pan.

title: quick and easy chicken
directions: Spray pan with Pam.
Place chicken in pan.
Put cheese on top. Combine soup and broth; add stuffing on top of cheese.
Pour liquid over stuffing.
Drizzle margarine on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: original pina colada
directions: Mix well in blender.
Garnish with a slice of pineapple and cherry.
Serves 2.
Cool and refreshing!

title: confetti noodle salad
directions: Combine first six ingredients; mix.
Combine yogurt and seasonings; add to noodle mixture.
Toss lightly.
Chill.

title: sausage balls
directions: Knead together and pinch off balls.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
