Ad eggs, one at a time and beat well. Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with milk.
Bake 80 minutes at 325°.
Don't forget to grease and flour pan.

title: m & m cookies
directions: Blend first 5 ingredients well.
Sift flour, baking soda and salt; add to mixture.
Stir in M & M's.
Bake on cookie sheet sprayed with non-stick spray, at 375 degrees for 10-12 minutes.

title: never fail meringue
directions: Combine cornstarch, sugar and water; cook until thick and clear.
Let cool.
Beat egg whites and vanilla until stiff. Continue beating while pouring cool mixture over whites.
Beat 5 minutes longer.
Spread on pie and bake at 400° for 5 to 7 minutes or to a golden brown.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: In a large pan, mix first three ingredients together well. Gradually add milk, stirring constantly over medium high heat.
Do not stir once it comes to a boil.
Turn down heat and put in candy thermometer until reaches "soft-ball" stage.
Remove from heat; add butter and vanilla.
Set pan in a little cold water in sink, being careful not to get any water in fudge.
Beat until dull.
Pour in a well buttered 10 x 10-inch pan.

title: christmas jello
directions: Make each package of jello according to directions on box in separate bowls.
Chill until set.
Using a pretty glass dish alternate tablespoons of red and green jello in a layer.
Spread Cool Whip over jello.
Continue the same pattern until dish is full.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle nuts on top.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Simmer first 4 ingredients for 3 minutes, then add Cheez Whiz and rice.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: perfect picnic chicken legs
directions: Combine ingredients and heat until sugar and margarine are dissolved.
Pour over large amount of chicken drumsticks. Marinate overnight.
Pour off most of the marinade.
Important! It foams, so leave only small amount in large baking dish.
(If I am baking for a cookout or large picnic, I use my turkey baker.) Cook at 325° for 20 minutes. Turn in marinade and bake 20 more minutes.
Cooked legs are mahogany colored and great cold.
I wrap a strip of aluminum foil around the top of each leg and stack in a serving dish because they are sticky.

title: guess what's in it cake
directions: Combine nuts and crackers in a bowl.
In another bowl, beat the egg whites until fluffy.
Gradually add sugar, baking powder and vanilla.
Mix this with crackers and nuts.
Put in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan; bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: lasagna
directions: In skillet, brown beef and onion in olive oil. Add tomatoes, paste, water, salt, sugar, garlic salt and pepper. Simmer, uncovered,
about 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: salt water taffy
directions: Put sugar and water in saucepan; stir to moisten sugar.
Then add rest of ingredients; cook from 265° to 270° (soft crack stage).
Pour into shallow, buttered pan.
As soon as candy is cool enough to handle, pull until white and porous.
Then quickly draw out into
a rope about half an inch in diameter.
Quickly cut into half-inch lengths, using kitchen shears with blades rubbed with oil or softened butter.
Lay each piece on small squares of heavy waxed paper.
Roll up and twist ends lightly.

title: cauliflower(yields 4 servings; pan size: 2-quart)
directions: Wash cauliflower.
Place undrained cauliflower in glass baking dish.
Microwave, tightly covered, on High for 7 to 8 minutes. Combine mayonnaise, prepared mustard and dry mustard in bowl; mix well.
Spread over cauliflower.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Microwave on High for 1 minute or just until cheese is melted.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients until tender.
Add soups, milk and cheese.
Melt all together.

title: springerle
directions: Beat eggs until light, stir in sugar a little at a time.
Beat 10 minutes.
Add lemon juice and melted butter.
Mix together in another bowl flour, salt and baking powder.
Add to first ingredients.
Dough should be fairly stiff.
Sprinkle flour on counter, roll dough out 1/2 inch thick.
Cut into shapes.
Lay on greased cookie sheets sprinkled with anise seed.
Leave sitting out for 24 hours before baking.
Bake at 350° (preheated) for 15-20 minutes.
Cookies should be very light in color, just tinted.

title: beef wellington bundles
directions: For pesto, combine 3 tablespoons oil, basil, parsley, Parmesan cheese and salt in a food processor. Cover and process until smooth; set aside. In a large skillet, brown steaks in 2 tablespoons butter and remaining oil for 5 - 6 minutes on
each side. Remove and keep warm. In the skillet, saute mushrooms until liquid is absorbed.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour
and nutmeg.
Add butter and beat until creamy.
Stir in eggs, buttermilk, lemon juice, vanilla and lemon rind.
Pour into pie crust.
Cook at 350° about 1 hour.

title: seven layer fiesta dip
directions: On a round pizza pan or round plate, spread beans (or dip). Layer mashed avocados over the beans and sprinkle with lemon juice.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning mix and spread over avocados.
Layer onions and tomatoes over the top for the 4th and 5th layers.
Spread olives on top and sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Garnish with sliced avocados.
Serve with chips to dip and you are set to go.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Best if prepared a day in advance.

title: english apple pie
directions: In medium bowl, beat butter and brown sugar with wooden spoon or electric mixer until pale and fluffy.
Stir in flour, 1 teaspoon cinnamon and water until smooth and thick.
Stir in pecans.
Mound apples in 9-inch pie plate.
Mix granulated sugar with remaining cinnamon (1 teaspoon) and sprinkle over apples.
Spoon pecan topping over apples in dollops.
Bake on lowest rack of preheated oven at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes or until apples are tender. Serve in bowls with cream.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 2-quart casserole dish, combine ground beef and onions with green beans and soup.
Mix well. Cover with mashed potatoes; bake for 20 minutes.
Cover potatoes with cheese slices and bake until cheese is melted.
Serves 4 to 6 people.
Makes great leftovers.

title: confetti fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 3 tablespoons syrup.
Toss pineapple, ham, cheese and oranges.
Place in lettuce-lined bowl. Chill.
Mix together mayonnaise, sour cream and reserved syrup. Serve as dressing with salad.
Makes 4 servings.

title: ham casserole
directions: Cover potatoes with water. Boil until done but not mushy. Drain. Melt butter in skillet. Add onion but do not brown. Add flour; stir until absorbed. Add milk and cheese. Cook until smooth and thick. Add salt, pepper, MSG and garlic salt; combine with ham and potatoes gently. Do not mash potato chunks. Place in greased casserole. Sprinkle with parsley flakes. Bake in 350° oven until slightly brown and bubbly. Yield: 5 servings.

title: zucchini-tomato skillet
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add onion, zucchini and mushrooms. Cook for 5 minutes.
Add tomato slices and all other ingredients except the Cheddar cheese.
Cook 4 minutes.
Remove from heat and sprinkle shredded Cheddar on top.
Serves 6.

title: whipped dessert topping
directions: In a bowl, combine nonfat dry milk, ice water and lemon juice. Use an electric mixer and beat until mixture is very stiff.
Beat in sugar and vanilla; beat until sugar is dissolved and mixture is smooth and creamy.
Serve at once.
Use as topping for desserts. Makes 1 2/3 cups.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: In a 2-quart casserole combine soup, milk, mustard and pepper. Stir in macaroni.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Saut onions, celery, carrots and garlic in margarine. Brown ground beef and drain. Add to onion mixture. Add salt, pepper, parsley and corn. Combine mixture with mushroom soup and stir on medium heat. Simmer 20 minutes. Pour mixture into 9 x 13-inch baking dish and cover with mashed potatoes. Top with cheese. Bake in oven for 30 to 45 minutes until bubbly. Let cool slightly. Cut into large squares.

title: mixed vegetables
directions: Put vegetables in casserole dish.
Sprinkle chopped onion on top.
Mix soup and sour cream and pour over onion and vegetables. Top with grated cheese.
Sprinkle crumbled crackers on top and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs.
Combine dry ingredients and add alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Drop from teaspoon onto a cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Ice with powdered sugar icing while warm.

title: pizza burger loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine first 9 ingredients and cook over medium heat for 15 minutes and cool 10 minutes.
Prepare hot roll mix as directed for pizza dough and roll into a 12-inch square on cookie sheet.
Spoon meat mixture down center third of dough to within 2 inches of each end.
Make cuts in dough on each side and fold over meat in a crisscross pattern to cover meat.
Brush top of dough with beaten egg and sprinkle with sesame seed.
Bake 30 minutes or top is golden brown.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Place pineapple in dish.
Mix sugar and flour; sprinkle over pineapple.
Pour 1/2 cup pineapple juice over mixture.
Place cheese on top.
Place crushed crackers in melted margarine and spread on top.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt butter.
Combine sugar, flour and cocoa and then mix with hot butter.
Add eggs.
Pour into two pie shells and bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Great served with ice cream.

title: quick blueberry slump
directions: Combine flour, salt and sugar in a medium bowl.
Add blueberries; toss gently.
Spoon into a lightly greased 8-inch square baking dish.
Sprinkle lemon juice over mixture and dot with butter.
Cut pastry to fit top.
Place over filling.
Make several cuts in pastry to allow steam to escape.
Bake at 450° for 18 to 20 minutes or until crust is golden.

title: green pepper jelly
directions: Grind peppers in blender with small amount of vinegar.
Add vinegar, sugar and food colorings.
Broil 5 to 10 minutes; add Certo and boil 1 minute.
Seal.
Makes 8 to 10 pints.
Good with crackers and cream cheese.

title: perfect chocolate fudge
directions: Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until soft ball stage on a candy thermometer.
Remove from heat; add butter.
Let set until lukewarm.
Add vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Add nuts and pour into buttered pan.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: In a large
bowl,
combine
all
ingredients except the candy Kisses.
Blend
at	low speed.
Shape into balls using a spoon to shape.
Roll balls in additional sugar.
Bake at 375° on ungreased cookie
sheet
for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from oven and top each cookie immediately with a candy Kiss.	Press down firmly so cookie
cracks
around
edges.
Makes
4 dozen cookies.

title: carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.

title: late summer pasta
directions: Combine all
ingredients,
except pasta.
Let stand one hour at room
temperature.
Cook
pasta, drain, then toss with tomato and cheese mixture.

title: fettucine ala alfredo
directions: Choose
a
pan
that
can accommodate all of the cooked fettucine
and the sauce.
Put 1/2 cup cream and the butter in the pan and simmer until the butter is melted.
Turn off heat. Cook fettucine
in
boiling
water, being very careful not to overcook. The
noodles
should be very firm as they will cook again when the sauce is added.
Drain the noodles and transfer to
pan containing cream.
Turn on low heat, add remainder of cream and all of the cheese, pepper and nutmeg.
Serve immediately with additional grated cheese on the side.

title: tomato relish
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook 3 1/2 hours until thick.
Pour in sterile jars.
Makes 6 quarts.

title: chilean tomato salad
directions: Cut tomatoes into wedges.
Dice onion.
Add rest of ingredients and toss.
Place in refrigerator for at least 1 hour or marinate overnight.
Serve cold.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix above well and add 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Pour into greased pan, 11 x 2 x 9-inch.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup chopped nuts mixed with 1/2 cup brown sugar on top of batter.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: french toast
directions: Arrange bread slices in a single layer in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Beat remaining ingredients except garnish until well blended and sugar is dissolved.
Pour over bread.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour or up to 24 hours, allowing bread to soak up liquid.
Heat oven to 425°.
Lightly grease a jelly roll pan. Transfer bread to prepared pan, making sure slices don't touch. Bake 12 to 15 minutes until puffed and lightly browned.
Dust with confectioners sugar and serve immediately.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit well.
Add cream, coconut and marshmallows. Refrigerate overnight.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients (except Ritz cracker crumbs) together in a greased casserole dish.
Top with Ritz cracker crumbs.
Add pats of butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour and salt together.
Cut shortening into flour mixture.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Drain Veg-All and empty into mixing bowl.
Chop celery, onions and chestnuts and add Veg-All.
Grate cheese and add to mixture along with the mayonnaise.
Mix well.

title: jeannine's no-bake chocolate cookies
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients.
Boil 5 minutes only.
Add 1/2 cup peanut butter and oatmeal; beat well.
Drop onto wax paper by teaspoonfuls until cool.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Prepare strawberry jello, substituting the water with hot pineapple juice and thawed strawberries.
Let set until cool. Spread evenly over Dream Whip filling and refrigerate until set.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Beat shortening and sugar.
Add 2 eggs and beat.
Blend together flour, soda and salt.
Add alternately flour mixture and buttermilk.
Add vanilla, nuts and banana.
Mix well and bake in greased and sugared loaf pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cranberry mango compote
directions: Combine cranberries, sugar and water in medium acid-resistant saucepan.
Bring to very slow simmer over medium heat.
Stir only to mix; avoid mashing the fruit.
Allow to cook about 30 minutes. Fruit will be very tender.
Add the mangoes, vanilla and Grand Marnier (or Triple Sec).
Return to simmer a few minutes.
Remove from heat and transfer to serving dish.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Keep refrigerated.

title: miniature mounds
directions: Mix butter, powdered sugar, Eagle Brand milk, coconut and vanilla.
Chill.
Form into balls.
Dip in melted chocolate Candi Quick and serve.

title: creamy cheese pie
directions: Beat cheese until smooth.
Gradually add sugar and continue beating.
Add sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spoon into crust.
Chill until set (about 4 hours).
Serve topped with sweetened fresh or canned fruit.

title: lorna doone cake
directions: Crush cookies and mix with melted stick of butter.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Let cool.
Mix ice cream, the two vanilla instant pudding packages and milk together. Spread on top of crushed cookie mixture.
Cool 15 minutes in the refrigerator.
Spread Cool Whip on top of pudding layer.
Freeze the 4 Heath bars and crush in blender.
Sprinkle on top of Cool Whip.
Freeze cake and let stand at room temperature for 10 minutes before serving.

title: italian sausage sub
directions: Brown sausage in oven, while sauteing peppers and onions in oil.
Cut cooked sausage into 2 inch chunks.
Place in baking pan; add peppers, onions, and sauce.
Bake 30
minutes at 350 degrees. Slice crusty sub rolls and top with sausage mixture and cheese. Wrap in foil and bake 12 minutes at 425 degrees.
Serve Hot.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions.
Drain; add cream cheese and 1/2 of the stick of butter.
Mix well and add salt and Tabasco sauce.
Pour into casserole dish and top with herb dressing.
Pour remaining melted butter over.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes until thoroughly heated.

title: "zucchini pie"
directions: Beat eggs until very light.
Add oil slowly, while beating. Add Bisquick, salt and pepper.
Fold in garlic, zucchini and cheese.
Place in a greased 2-quart low casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until bubbly.

title: microwave hot potato salad(german)
directions: Combine
bacon and onion in 8-inch round dish.	Cook at High 3
to
minutes;	stir
occasionally.
Stir
in flour, vinegar, sugar,
celery seed, salt and pepper.
Add potatoes. Cook at High 4 to 5 minutes; stir.
Serve warm.

title: broccoli-ham hot dish
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
Spoon rice into a 13 x 9-inch Pyrex. Place broccoli over rice, coat bread crumbs with 2 tablespoons of oleo and set aside.
In 4 tablespoons oleo, saute onion, add flour, salt and pepper; cook until bubbly.
Stir in milk and continue cooking until thick, add ham to broccoli and rice mixture; pour sauce over and sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: barbecue shrimp
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large black skillet on top of stove.
Add shrimp.
Cook, covered, 5 to 10 minutes (according to size).
Stir constantly.
Do not overcook; it will make them hard to peel.

title: believe it or not cake
directions: *Skip if using self-rising flour.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix vegetables, water chestnuts, mayonnaise, onion and cheese. Spread in 2-quart baking dish.
Top with layer of crushed crackers; dot with margarine.
Cover and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Or microwave, uncovered, 10 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Save the broth.
Cut chicken up into pieces.
Make the stuffing according to directions, but instead of using water, use chicken broth.
Mix the soup with chicken broth. Next, layer a casserole dish with chicken, stuffing and broth.
Do this until the stuffing is on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix pineapple and vanilla pudding in bowl.
Add sour cream; fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into pie shells and set in icebox for several hours.
Brown pie shells and cool.

title: easy potato bake
directions: In a 2-quart baking dish (12 x 8-inch), loosely arrange potatoes.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: no cook banana pudding
directions: **Amount depends on size of pan chosen.

title: toad in the hole
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
With fork, prick 1 pound sausage links. Place in greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake 15 minutes or until well browned.
Turn once.
In blender on low speed, blend eggs, milk, flour, thyme and salt until smooth.
Pour off all but 1/4 cup of fat from links.
Pour batter over links; return to oven for 25 minutes until browned crust.

title: pichelsteiner stew(german stew)
directions: Cut meat and potatoes into pieces.
Dice, slice or cut other vegetables into strips.
Place slices of marrow on bottom of a heatproof casserole or Dutch oven, or, if using lard instead of marrow, brush casserole with lard.
Arrange alternate layers of meat, potatoes and the other vegetables in the casserole.
Season each layer with salt, pepper and herbs.
Add bay leaf.

title: red hot chili
directions: Brown
the
meat and saute the onions.
Add this to the tomatoes in a large pot.
Cook for 30 minutes.
Add all spices and cook
for
1 1/2 hours.
Mix the flour and maize into the water. Stir
slowly until the chili mixture thickens.
Simmer slowly for 1/2 hour.
Stir frequently.

title: shrimp marinade
directions: Peel shrimp. Stir together all the above ingredients. Marinade in refrigerator no longer than 2 hours.
Grill 3 minutes per side.
Brush with marinade while cooking. Leftovers are great cold with crackers.

title: sweet potato corn chowder
directions: In 4-quart pan saute bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon with slotted spoon and set aside.
Add onion, red pepper, leek, thyme, marjoram, salt and pepper to bacon drippings.
Saute, stirring occasionally, for 10 minutes.
Add sweet potatoes, corn, chicken broth and 2 1/2 cups water.
Cook until potatoes are tender, 15 to 20 minutes.
Mix cornstarch with 1/2 cup water and stir into soup. Heat to boiling and cook until thickened.
Reduce heat and stir in cream and bacon, heat just until bubbles appear at sides of pan.

title: salami
directions: Mix well.
Knead for 10 minutes.
Store in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Knead 10 minutes again.
Store in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Shape in 5 or 6 loaves and place on broiler pan.
Bake 4 hours at 150°; turn loaves over and bake 4 hours more.
Will keep up to 3 to 4 weeks in refrigerator.

title: chicken-cranberry casserole
directions: Place Chicken in casserole.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook asparagus; make cream sauce with butter, flour, soup and liquid.
Add asparagus and remaining ingredients, except noodles. Pour into a 2-quart greased casserole; top with noodles and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: japanese fruit cake pie
directions: Beat eggs with eggbeater.
Add all ingredients; mix well.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 300° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: onion cheese supper bread
directions: Cook onions in small amount of hot fat until clear, not brown. Combine egg and milk; add to biscuit mix. Stir only until moistened. Add onion, half the cheese and parsley. Spread dough on greased 8-inch square pan. Sprinkle remaining cheese. Drizzle melted butter on top. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes until pick comes out clean. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread pineapple and cherry pie filling evenly in ungreased 9 1/2 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle cake mix evenly over pineapple and pie filling.
Sprinkle with nuts and margarine on top.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
You can substitute other fruits for pineapple and cherry pie filling.
Cranberry is not as sweet as cherry.

title: french salad dressing
directions: Blend well in blender or mixer. Makes 3 cups.

title: chocolate refrigerator cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add melted chocolate and vanilla; mix well.
Stir in nuts.
Add sifted dry ingredients to creamed mixture alternately with sour milk.

title: pesto stuffed mushrooms
directions: Core mushrooms to make cups.
Combine remaining ingredients and stuff mushrooms.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Remove from heat and serve.

title: flan
directions: Caramelize sugar at bottom of pan; set aside and let harden. Beat all above ingredients well in a blender or mixer.
Pour in caramelized pan; set this pan in a pan of water to bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Let cool; run knife around edge of pan; invert on a plate.

title: parmesan herb bread
directions: Mix Parmesan cheese, parsley, garlic and basil together. Butter bread and sprinkle with Parmesan mixture.
Cook under broiler until brown (425°).

title: spiced tea mix
directions: Combine all ingredients.
To Drink:
For 1 cup, use 1 1/2 teaspoons mix and 3/4 cup hot water.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix cocoa with flour, sugar and salt.
Add egg yolks and milk, mixing well.
Then add margarine.
Cook in double boiler until thick.
Add vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Cover with meringue and brown.

title: easy barbecue pork roast
directions: Pour water into a slow cooker; add roast and salt.
In a bowl combine brown sugar and barbecue sauce.
Pour over roast.
Slow cook on high for 1 hour; then continue to cook on low until fork tender (5 to 6 hours).

title: tuna casserole
directions: In saucepan, combine all ingredients, except rice; bring to boil. Stir in rice, then pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole. Cover and bake 10 minutes in moderate 375° oven. If desired, top with bread crumbs and grated Parmesan cheese. Brown under broiler. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: warm bloody mary
directions: Combine all ingredients in 1 1/2-quart bowl.
Microwave 3 1/2 minutes on Medium.
Stir twice; don't boil.
Remove cloves and serve.
Makes 1 quart.

title: chili spaghetti dinner for 2
directions: In saucepan cook sausage, onion and carrot until meat is browned.
Drain off fat.
Stir in tomato juice, kidney beans, salt, chili powder and pepper.
Place uncooked spaghetti in a 1-quart casserole.
Stir in meat mixture.
Bake uncovered in 375° oven for 55 to 60 minutes or until spaghetti is tender, stirring twice.
Makes 2 or 3 servings.

title: chinese noodles
directions: Note:
You
can
use 1 to packages of chop suey vegetables in place of the fresh vegetables, if you wish.

title: dalma (armenian stuffed vegetables)
directions: Cut squash in half and remove pulp.
Cut near the top of the peppers and remove the seeds.
Save the tops.
Cut near the top of the tomatoes, not all the way off.
Scoop the pulp from tomatoes and reserve.
Mix meat with uncooked rice, onions, parsley, dill, salt, pepper and chopped pulp from 3 tomatoes and 3 squash.
Stuff vegetables loosely (allowing for expansion).
Replace pepper tops. Arrange filled vegetables in a 2-quart casserole dish, with cover.
Put tomatoes on top of peppers and squash.

title: peanut rolls
directions: Beat egg yolks; add 3/4 cup sugar and salt; beat 5 minutes, then add water.
In separate bowl, beat egg whites until stiff and add remaining 3/4 cup sugar.
Stir with egg yolk mixture and fold in flour and baking powder.
Bake in 350° oven in 9 x 13-inch pan for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Add oil and beaten eggs.
Mix thoroughly with strawberries and nuts.
Pour into two greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fried oysters
directions: Mix cornmeal and flour to make a batter.
Rinse oysters, drain on paper towel.
Add salt and pepper prior to dredging in batter.
Deep fry until golden brown.

title: zucchini bread(for 2 loaves)
directions: Mix all together; pour into 2 loaf pans sprayed with nonstick spray.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Also makes great cupcakes and just need to bake about 25 minutes.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Drain salmon into measuring cup. Add enough milk to salmon liquid to make 3/4 cup. Flake salmon, removing skin. Blend in egg. Stir in rest of ingredients. Spoon into lightly greased loaf pan or 1-quart baking dish. Bake 45 minutes at 350°. If you can mash the salmon bones and add to the mixture, your family will obtain additional calcium. Usually these are soft and easily mashed. Serves 4 to 6.

title: orange sherbet
directions: Combine sugar and water. Bring to boiling point and boil for 5 minutes. Dissolve the softened gelatin in the hot syrup. Beat egg whites until stiff.
Pour the syrup gradually over the beaten whites, beating constantly. Add fruit juices.
Pour into freezing tray and freeze at coldest temperature. When almost frozen, remove to chilled bowl and beat well. Return to tray and freeze until firm.

title: yummy chicken
directions: Mix cooked chicken and bread crumbs and place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine eggs, Worcestershire sauce, salt, paprika and chicken broth.
Pour this over chicken mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.
Heat water and oleo.
Add Pepperidge Farm stuffing crumbs.
Sprinkle over pan of chicken mixture.
Bake uncovered 1 1/4 hours at 325°.
Serve with golden chicken gravy.
(I use instant cream of chicken soup for gravy.)

title: cheddar corn muffins
directions: Mix together all ingredients just until combined.
Do not overstir.
Bake in greased muffin tins, preheated at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes until brown.

title: shrimp loaf
directions: Have cheese at room temperature.
Heat soup to boiling and add cream cheese, stirring constantly until dissolved.
Dissolve gelatin in 1/2 cup cold water.
Add to soup and cream cheese mixture.
Add juice of 1 lemon if desired.
Allow to cool.
Add mayonnaise.
Stir well.
Add shrimp, onions and celery.
Pour into oiled mold or loaf pan.
Refrigerate.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onion in pastry shell.
Beat eggs slightly; beat in remaining ingredients.
Pour cream mixture into pie shell.
Bake 15 minutes at 425°.
Reduce oven temperature to 300° and bake 30 minutes longer.
Check for doneness with a knife in the center.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: apple charlotte
directions: Line a greased mold with bread slices, brushed with melted butter.
Fill center with stewed apples and add almonds.
Cover top with slices of bread, buttered, and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: ham fried rice
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Saute green onions, celery and pepper in 1/2 cup oil.
Cook until tender.
Add Spam and rice and 1/2 cup soy sauce.
Cover pan and let cook for 15-20 minutes.

title: poppy seed tart
directions: Make crust and pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake crust 10 to 15 minutes and cool.
Pour filling into crust and refrigerate.

title: low cholesterol pumpkin pie
directions: Bake at 450° for 10 minutes; 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 2 (9-inch) pies; 100 calories per slice.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a greased 2 quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
For a variation, you may want to top the dressing with grated Cheddar cheese before baking.

title: scalloped carrots
directions: Place carrots in saucepan.
Cover with water.
Cook until crisp-tender.

title: layered salad
directions: Use a large, clear bowl.
Mix mayonnaise and sugar until smooth.
Boil peas 3 minutes and let cool.
Layer 1/2 of lettuce, carrots, celery, lettuce, radishes, zucchini, onions, cooled peas, mayo and sugar and cheese.
Let stand 8 to 12 hours.
Add tomato wedges, egg wedges and crumbled bacon.
Serves 20 to 25 people.

title: toffee squares
directions: Cream butter and sugar, add beaten egg and vanilla.
Add flour and salt.
Spread on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Spread 1 pound shaved chocolate on top and return to oven until melted.
Cut into squares while warm.
Very important!

title: sweet relish
directions: Grind vegetables- sprinkle with salt, let stand overnight. Rinse and drain.
Combine rest of ingredients.
Pour over vegetable mixture.
Heat to boiling.
Simmer 3 minutes.
Seal in hot, sterilized jars.

title: hot milk sponge cake
directions: Beat eggs until light yellow; add sugar.
Beat at low speed until well mixed.
Add flour and baking powder.
Add cooled milk, butter and vanilla.
Bake at 350°.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix peanuts, sugar, corn syrup and salt in a glass bowl. Microwave 7 to 9 minutes on High.
Mixture should be bubbling and peanuts browned.
Quickly stir in margarine and vanilla.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes longer.
Add baking soda and stir quickly, just until foamy.
Pour immediately on greased baking sheet.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: green "gobble de' gook"
directions: Stir first three ingredients together well.
Chill.
Serve topped with Grape-Nuts.
Sprinkle on top.

title: veggie roll-up
directions: Boil
asparagus and carrots until tender.
Add salt and pepper to
beef
and
roll
in flour.
Roll all vegetables up inside the slice
of
beef.
Fry in oil, rolling in pan until brown on
all sides.
Cut roll-ups in half and serve on a bed of lettuce.
Mix soy sauce and cooking wine together.
Pour on roll-ups and serve.

title: pineapple dessert
directions: Combine crumbs, sugar and melted butter in bowl.
Press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill.

title: baked peaches and pears
directions: Drain 1/2 of juice from fruit and discard.
Combine fruit, cinnamon and 1 cup of bread crumbs.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup bread crumbs.
Dot with margarine. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, or until lightly browned.

title: cheese cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Using electric mixer, mix together cream cheese, sour cream and sugar until creamy.
Blend in remaining ingredients, except cinnamon.
Pour mixture into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch glass dish.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top of mixture.
Place in oven and cook for 1 hour.
Turn off oven, leaving cake to cool in unopened oven for 1 hour.
Do not open door of oven until cake is cooled.

title: nut fingers
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Add flour gradually. Add nuts and mix well with hands.
Pinch off small amounts of dough and shape.
Bake on baking sheet at about 350° until slightly brown.
When cool, roll in confectioners sugar.

title: chicken rice bake
directions: Put rice in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex pan and pour onion soup over this, then place chicken pieces over this.
Next, put mushroom soup over chicken.
Place in a 350° oven for about 1 hour.

title: perpetual muffins
directions: Combine all ingredients in a very large mixing bowl.
Store in refrigerator with a seal on.
Can keep up to 4 weeks in refrigerator.
Use as desired.
Fill muffin cup 2/3 full. Bake in muffin tins in a 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: tossed taco salad
directions: Add ground beef while still hot.
Toss all together.
Almost a meal in itself.

title: twice baked potatoes(lo-fat)
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Bake the potatoes about 1 hour or until tender. Cut thin lengthwise slice from top of each potato.
Scoop out potato, leaving a thin shell.
Mash the potatoes until no lumps remain. Beat in remaining ingredients, except paprika, until fluffy. Sprinkle with paprika.
Place shells on ungreased cookie sheet. Fill shells with potato mixture. Bake, uncovered, about 20 minutes or until filling is golden brown.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chili pie or dip
directions: Brown hamburger in large saucepan; drain fat.
Pour in all other ingredients, except cheese.
Divide evenly into 3 pie thins or 1 large casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes. May be frozen and reheated for serving.
Cheese should be added before baking or before reheating.
Very good served with corn chips.

title: quick cherry cobbler
directions: In round, deep pie pan, put margarine and place in 425° oven to melt.
While margarine is melting, mix together the flour, sugar and sweet milk; mix well.
Pour this mixture over melted margarine, but do not stir.
Pour can of cherry pie filling in pan; do not stir.
Bake 25 minutes at 425° or until crust is brown.
(Crust will not rise to top if a square pan is used.)

title: hamburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Brown ground beef in large skillet; add onion and green pepper.
Drain.
Stir in tomato sauce, salt and garlic.
Remove from heat.
Prepare cornbread according to package directions.
Spread batter over top of meat mixture evenly.
Place in oven for 15 minutes or until cornbread is golden brown.
Remove and let stand for 5 minutes.
Place plate over skillet and invert pie onto serving plate; cut in wedges.
Serve with grated cheese sprinkled over top.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and salt to taste.
Crush crackers and spread on top, then pour melted butter on and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix ingredients and pour into greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes.
Let cool.

title: 3 in 1 cookie dough
directions: Combine flour and baking soda.
Mix remaining ingredients. Drop on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: linguine, broccoli and ham bake
directions: Melt butter. Stir in flour.
Gradually add milk, stirring until thick. Stir in 1/3 cup Parmesan and garlic.
Remove from heat. In a 2-quart casserole dish, combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons Parmesan over top. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: mini sausage calzones
directions: Preheat oven to 425 degrees. Grease a baking sheet. Divide dough into 8 portions. Heat a large skillet over medium heat; add sausage and cook until brown and crumbly. Drain fat, stir in onion, garlic, basil, oregano and tomato sauce. Simmer for 10 minutes. Roll each piece of dough into a 5-inch circle. Spoon sausage mixture onto each circle; sprinkle with cheese. Moisten edges of dough with water. Fold dough over to enclose filling. Press to seal using tines of fork. Place on baking sheet. Beat egg with milk and brush over calzones. Bake for about 15 minutes or until golden brown. Serve immediately. Makes 8 servings.

title: hot appetizer pie
directions: Soften the cream cheese and blend with milk.
Mix in other ingredients, except nuts.
Put into an 8-inch glass pie plate. Spread nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: cheesy corn bread
directions: Combine all ingredients, stirring by hand.
Pour into well-greased 8-inch square pan or round cake pan.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes until well browned.
Allow to stand 10 minutes before cutting into squares or slices.
Serves 6.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Blend together beef, eggs, 1 tablespoon cornstarch, onion, pepper, nutmeg, salt and garlic.
Form into 1 inch balls.
Heat oil in skillet and brown meatballs on all sides.
In a large saucepan, add remaining cornstarch to pineapple juice and soy sauce, vinegar, water and brown sugar.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly. Add meatballs, fruit and green pepper and cook 5 minutes or until fruit is well heated.
Serve sprinkled with chopped or slivered almonds.

title: french met tea
directions: *May substitute mint tea bags.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients. Add remaining. Stir until well blended.
Stir in nuts. Bake in well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes or until tests done.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except broccoli, and refrigerate two to three hours.
Before serving, add broccoli.
Delicious!

title: chopandiangas
directions: Dip tortillas in hot fat to soften; blot excess fat from tortillas with paper towels.
Arrange 6 tortillas in a 13 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: virginia chicken-apple salad
directions: Sprinkle apples with 1 tablespoon lemon juice. Combine first 6 ingredients.
Combine remaining lemon juice and next 3 ingredients.
Fold the whipped cream mixture into the chicken mixture.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Combine tomatoes, toasted bread cubes, onion, salt, sugar and basil.
Place in 1 1/2-quart greased casserole dish, top with margarine.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients, then roll into a ball and roll into chopped chives.
Wrap in cellophane and refrigerate overnight.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pinch a small portion of mixture and roll into a ball.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet and press with a fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: lemon raspberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Line 12 muffin cups with paper baking cups.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Mix well.
In a small bowl, combine half and half, oil, lemon extract and eggs; blend well. Add to dry ingredients; stir until dry ingredients are just moistened.
Carefully fold in raspberries. Fill cups 3/4 full. Bake for 18 to 23 minutes or until golden brown. Cool for 5 minutes. Remove from pan.
Yields 12 muffins.

title: ham delights
directions: Blend ham and cheese.
Put into large bowl.
Add mustard, poppy seed, onion, Worcestershire sauce and margarine.
Mix well. Split open rolls and put mixture in (about 1/2 tablespoon).
Cover with foil and place biscuits in oven on warm until biscuits are warm.
Serve while hot.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix sugar and flour together.
Add vinegar, water and mustard.
Bring to a boil and cool.
Mix all ingredients together and allow to sit several hours before serving.

title: barbecued pork chops or chicken
directions: Put sliced onions in Pyrex dish. Place meat on onion. Salt and pepper to taste. Combine all other ingredients in saucepan and bring to boil. Simmer 5 minutes. Pour over meat. Cover. Place in oven and cook at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: never fail divinity
directions: Boil sugar, water and salt until mixture forms a hard ball in cold water.
Place Marshmallow Creme in bowl.
Stir in hot mixture.
Continue stirring until slightly stiff.
Fold in nuts and vanilla.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: herbed rice pilaf
directions: In a skillet, saute rice, celery and onion in butter until the rice is lightly browned and the vegetables are tender.
Spoon into a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Combine all remaining ingredients.
Pour over rice mixture.
Cover and bake at 325° for 50 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: rhubarb custard for pie
directions: Mix well and put rhubarb in last.
Pour into pie crust and cover with top crust.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: daisy's deviled crab
directions: Mix all ingredients except margarine and paprika.
Place in individual crab shells.
Dot each one with margarine and sprinkle with paprika.
Put in the broiler until margarine is melted and they are golden brown.
If you do not have crab shells you can use aluminum ones that you get from any seafood department or put in a shallow baking dish.

title: cake in a bowl
directions: Other fruit can also be added (pineapple, peaches, kiwi or blueberries).

title: egg curry
directions: Heat oil in large pan.
Fry onions till golden brown.
Mix garlic, ginger, almonds, chili powder, turmeric and coriander with a little water and grind into a paste.
Reduce heat and add the spice paste and whole dried chilies.
Fry gently for a few minutes.
Add the tomatoes, bay leaves, coconut mixture, sultanas and salt.
Allow to simmer for about 15 minutes, adding more water if necessary.
Check the seasonings and adjust if needed, then add egg halves, yolk side up.
Cover the eggs with the sauce and simmer for about 5 minutes.
Serve hot garnished with rice, banana slices, toasted coconut and chutney.
This sauce is also very good with cooked cubed chicken.

title: red rice
directions: Brown bacon in large pan, remove and set aside.
Drain all but 2 tablespoons drippings.
Saute rice in drippings briefly.
Add remaining ingredients; stir until well combined.
Bring to boil and turn down to low.
Cover and simmer 20 to 25 minutes until liquid is absorbed and rice is tender.
Stir in cooked bacon and serve. Serves 6 to 8.

title: spiced cider punch
directions: Boil the first 3 ingredients 5 minutes.
Put spices in cheesecloth bag and boil with sugar and water, then let stand 1 hour.
Serve steaming hot in mugs.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients together and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool.
Serve plain or with Cool Whip topping.

title: party pizza
directions: Cook sausage and drain off grease.
Mix all ingredients (except bread) and spread on bread slices.
Place slices in hot oven until cheese is melted.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Cream sugar and lard.
Beat in eggs; add blackberries.
Sift flour, soda, spices and salt together.
Then add to first mixture. Beat 3 minutes.
Bake in 2 large or 3 small layer pans for 30 minutes at 350°.
Frost with Caramel Icing.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine all ingredients and drop by spoonfuls into deep, hot fat.
Cook until they float.
Remove and drain.

title: apple-berry cake
directions: Sprinkle marshmallows over bottom of a glass baking dish, set aside.
Combine applesauce, strawberries and dry Jell-O.
Set aside.
Combine dry ingredients, blend in shortening, milk, eggs and vanilla.
Pour batter over marshmallows, then spoon fruit mixture over batter.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until cake is done.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: vegetarian meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except tomato juice, garlic and Italian seasonings; mixture should be moist, never runny.
Form into little balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: carrots and grapes
directions: Saute carrots, cut in thick diagonal slices, in margarine for a few minutes. Sprinkle carrots with sugar and cook, stirring for a few minutes. Add vodka and water.
When the carrots are almost tender, add grapes.
Cover pan and continue to cook until carrots are tender. Season with salt and pepper to taste.

title: raisin sauce
directions: Boil water, raisins, sugar and salt 15 minutes.
Melt butter and stir into flour.
Cook slowly, stirring, until it boils.
Add flavoring.
Yields 1 2/3 cups.

title: crock-pot chicken-n-rice
directions: Use salt, pepper and garlic salt as desired.
Place all in a crock-pot on low heat.
Cook 8 to 9 hours.
Prepare rice and spoon ingredients over hot rice for great meat with beans, salad and rolls.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in a 9 x 13-inch casserole for 30 minutes at 350°.
Freezes well.

title: "dump" salad
directions: Dump all into bowl.
Mix and refrigerate.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Combine sugar, chocolate, corn syrup, milk and salt in a saucepan.
Cook on low heat until sugar dissolves.
Cook on medium heat until mixture reaches soft ball stage.
Remove from heat. Add butter and vanilla.
Cool until mixture is lukewarm.
Beat with a wooden spoon until it loses its gloss.
Pour onto buttered pan.
Let it set until firm.

title: ginny's blueberry muffins
directions: Mix Bisquick and sugar.
Add egg and sour cream.
Mix well and add blueberries.
Mix 1 teaspoon grated lemon rind and 1 tablespoon sugar and put on top of muffins.
Bake at 425° approximately 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sweet potato muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease muffin tins.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and mix well.
Blend in sweet potatoes.
Sift the dry ingredients.
Add alternately with the milk.
Fold in nuts and raisins.
Fill muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake 25 minutes.

title: sauteed chicken livers
directions: Saute chicken livers in butter 5 minutes or until brown. Remove livers and drain on paper towels, reserving drippings in skillet.
Saute mushrooms and onions in drippings until onion is golden.
Add salt, tomatoes, wine, parsley and Worcestershire sauce; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cook 5 minutes, stirring often.
Add livers, simmer 5 additional minutes.
Serve over rice. Yields 4 servings.

title: wonderful french dressing
directions: Shake thoroughly in a glass jar or partially empty catsup bottle.
Excellent for diabetics when using artificial sweetener. Yield:
1 1/2 cups.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain all beans and mix all ingredients together and refrigerate overnight.

title: "beef" noodle dish
directions: Put Vegeburger in oil in large skillet.
Add next 6 ingredients and 1/2 cup water.
Bring to boil and simmer 10 minutes.
Add to 1 to 2 cups water to cover burger; bring to boil and add noodles.
Stir; cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until noodles are very tender.
Add more water if necessary.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs; add remaining ingredients.
Pour into buttered or sprayed casserole and sit in pan of boiling water.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in a 375° oven for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: oven-fried chicken
directions: Mix garlic salt and pepper with potato chips.
Dip chicken in melted butter and roll in chips.
Place skin side up, sides not touching, in greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with any remaining crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until done.
Do not turn.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Lightly brown meat; add onion and cook until tender.
Add seasonings, beans and soup.
Pour in casserole dish.
Cook 5 medium potatoes until done.
Prepare as for mashed potatoes.
Add egg, milk and seasoning.
Drop in mounds over meat.
If desired, sprinkle 1/2 cup shredded cheese over top.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Saute onions and celery.
Mix Cheez Whiz, mushroom soup, milk and broccoli.
Mix together; add rice.
Bake 30 minutes in a 400° oven in a 7 x 11-inch pan.
May add diced ham or chicken before baking.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Mix sugar and butter; add beaten egg and yeast.
Add self-rising flour.
Drop by spoonfuls in greased muffin tins to 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Will keep in airtight container for one week.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Spread on a serving plate. Pour shrimp sauce on top and spread over mixture.
Garnish center with parsley; surround with crackers.

title: delicious pickles
directions: Mix together sugar, vinegar, salt and celery seed; pour over vegetables after they have been placed in a glass 1 gallon jar. Refrigerate overnight.
Can be served next day.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: shrimp wrapped in seaweed
directions: Shell
and split shrimp, leaving tail intact.
Marinate for 15 minutes
in
mixture
of
sake,
1/2 teaspoon salt and ginger. Pat
marinated
shrimp
dry
with
paper towel.
Make paste (surumi)
by
chopping
fish fillet together with sake, green onion,
teaspoon
salt, sugar, pepper, sesame oil, cornstarch and
water chestnuts, using a food processor.
Cut nori
sheets into
x 2 1/2-inch, depending on size of shrimp.
Place shrimp in middle of nori; top with 1 tablespoon of above paste. Fold over; seal nori with paste made of flour and
water.
Coat with cornstarch, dip in beaten egg, then in panko or bread crumbs. Set aside.
Deep fry turning once.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cream cheese until soft and fluffy. Beat in peanut butter and sugar. Slowly add milk, beating until well blended. Fold topping into mixture after it's thawed. Ladle into pie crust. Sprinkle with nuts. Freeze until firm.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs; gradually beat in sugar, then oil.
Alternate dry ingredients with zucchini.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Makes 2 large loaves.
Grease loaf pans before filling with batter.

title: 2 minute micro fudge
directions: In 2-quart casserole, mix first 5 ingredients (don't worry if not fully blended).
Put butter and peanut butter on top. Microwave on High for
2 minutes.
Stir vigorously.
Pour into buttered 8-inch square casserole.
Pat down and cool in refrigerator.
Cut into squares.

title: banana-strawberry-orange pops
directions: You will also need 4 or 5 small paper cups and 4 or 5 popsicle sticks.

title: coconut pies
directions: In a double boiler, combine sugar, egg yolks and flour.
Add milk gradually.
When this mixture gets hot, put in marshmallows, vanilla and 1/2 can of coconut.
Pour into baked pie shells.

title: autumn leaf pumpkin pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Beat well with rotary beater until smooth.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and bake for approximately 30 minutes longer or until filling is just set in center.
Cool.
Decorate with cheese leaves before serving.

title: tandy cakes
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients well.
Pour into greased 17 x 11-inch jelly roll pan (if you use 15 x 10-inch, you get a thicker cake). Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
As soon as removed from oven, spread peanut butter on top of hot cake evenly.
Refrigerate 1/2 hour. Melt Hershey bars and spread over cooled cake.
Refrigerate until set.
Cut into small bars and serve.

title: pistachio delight
directions: Mix dry pudding mix with fruit cocktail and juice.
Fold in Cool Whip and pecans.
Chill.

title: 7 layer banana cake
directions: With a fork, mix graham crackers with melted butter.
Press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan and chill.

title: applesauce jam cake
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients.
Set aside.
Cream together second five ingredients.
Add to other mixture, then add remaining ingredients.
Bake 50 -60 minutes or until done in 325 degree oven.

title: beefy cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese and mayo in bowl until smooth.
Add next 3 ingredients.
Shape into ball.
Chill until firm.
Serve with crackers.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening or butter.
Add egg yolks and beat thoroughly.
Add milk, soda, baking powder and bananas.
Add flour, egg whites (not beaten) and vanilla.
Place in 3 well-greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes.
Remove and ice with butter icing, spreading generously between layers as well as the outside.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Sift and measure flour.
Sift again with salt and baking soda. Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each egg.
Add flavoring.
Add dry ingredients, alternating with sour cream.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in salt water until tender, then drain. While macaroni is still hot add 1 stick margarine and let cool.

title: citric punch
directions: Dissolve crystals in 2-quarts boiling water.
Let set for 24 hours.
Mix orange juice, pineapple juice, sugar and 2-quarts water together and mix well.
Combine both mixtures and mix thoroughly.
Divide into three containers and freeze.

title: rich and charlie salad
directions: Mix ingredients and let sit 1/2 hour before serving.
Serves 6.

title: peanut butter creams
directions: Mix sugar, margarine and peanut butter together and roll into small (1-inch) balls.
(May need to chill if weather or kitchen is warm.)
Melt chocolate and wax in top of double boiler or over water in small pan.
Make a dipper (like an egg dipper, base at right angle to the handle) and dip into chocolate.
Place on waxed paper and chill to set.
You may use a fork or toothpick instead of dipper.
Recipe takes time, but is very simple and much loved.

title: ribbon layered lemon pie
directions: In medium pan, melt butter.
Stir in lemon juice, sugar and salt; stir until sugar is dissolved.
Pour 1/2 hot mixture into eggs, stirring.
Return all to saucepan; cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Chill.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix and boil first 4 ingredients 4 or 5 minutes and then add other 4 ingredients.
Stir well and drop on wax paper with spoon.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Melt caramels with 1/3 cup evaporated milk in double boiler. Mix cake mix with butter and the rest of the evaporated milk. Spread half of dough into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
After the 10 minutes, put chocolate chips over baked dough and follow with caramel mixture.
Next, spread the rest of dough on top and bake 15 to 18 minutes at 350°. Refrigerate for 1 hour and cut into bars.

title: crab dip
directions: Heat the cream cheese until smooth.
Stir in the remaining ingredients.
Spoon into small ovenproof dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbling.
Makes 1 cup.

title: vanilla refrigerator cookies
directions: Mix sugar, butter, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour, salt, soda and nuts.
Shape dough into rolls 1 1/2-inches in diameter. Wrap and chill at least 4 hours.
Slice cookies 1/4-inch wide and place 1 inch apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Immediately remove from baking sheet and cool.

title: taco meat loaf
directions: Combine meat, tomato sauce, bread crumbs, onion, bell pepper, chiles, egg and taco seasoning mix in a large bowl, mixing well. Press half of the mixture into a 9 x 5 x 3-inch glass pan.
Top with cheese.
Press remaining mixture on top of cheese.
Cover with heavy-duty plastic wrap and vent to allow steam to escape. Microwave on High for 15 minutes.
Invert on serving plate and top with sour cream.
Serve with corn chips.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown the ground beef with taco seasoning as directed.
Strain and let cool.
In a 9 x 12-inch pan, layer sour cream.
Top with ground beef, then refried beans (optional), then top with lettuce, tomatoes, olives (optional) and cheese.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Serve with chips.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook tomatoes until tender.
Put through blender, then through colander to get juice.
Add garlic powder, onions, peppers, oil, sugar, salt, oregano, basil and tomato paste.
Bring to a boil. Boil for 45 minutes.
Pour in hot, sterilized jars.
Pressure for 5 minutes at 5 pound pressure in cooker.

title: pickled daikon
directions: Slice carrot into 1/16-inch thick rounds.
Cut daikon into 1 1/2-inch thick rounds.

Place it between a pair of chopsticks, slice it into 1/10-inch thick, just slice down to the chopsticks. Then turn it around and cut it in the same way across the slits. Sprinkle salt on carrot and daikon; stir up well by hand.
Wait 10 to 15 minutes, until they are tender, then marinate in sugar, water, pepper and rice vinegar mixture overnight or more.
Remove daikon, open like a flower and place a carrot slice in each one.

title: mystery pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff; gradually add sugar, vanilla and baking powder and beat until thick.
Fold in nuts and crackers. Pour into greased pie pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool and spread top with Cool Whip.
Leave in refrigerator for 12 to 24 hours before serving.

title: heavenly carrot soup
directions: Heat oil in cooker.
Saute leeks for 2 minutes.
Add carrots, potatoes, celery, stock and tarragon.
Cook on stove top for 25 to 30 minutes, until vegetables are soft.
(Bring to a boil, then simmer, covered).
Or, if using pressure cooker, maintain pressure at high for 5 minutes.
Reduce pressure with quick release method. Puree soup in batches in blender or food processor.
Add tablespoon of Miso into final batch.
Return to cooker to reheat. Garnish with 1/4 cup chopped watercress and croutons before serving.

title: apple crisp
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients in order and let stand 15 minutes.
Then add the flour, soda, raisins or nuts.

title: quick tricks with biscuits
directions: Roll each biscuit into 8-inch lengths.
Dip in melted butter and dip or roll into mixture of cinnamon, sugar and chopped nuts. Shape in coil on greased baking sheet.
Bake in 450° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: caramel corn
directions: Put popcorn in a roasting pan.
Combine brown sugar, corn syrup and margarine in a 1 1/2-quart saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture boils.
Reduce heat to medium-low and cook, without stirring, for 5 more minutes.
Remove from heat. Add vanilla and baking soda.
Stir until mixed.
Pour mixture over popcorn and gently stir to coat.
Bake in a 325° oven for 15 minutes; stir.
Bake another 5 minutes.
Transfer popcorn to large piece of foil to cool.
Break into clusters.
Store tightly covered.

title: peach crisp
directions: Peel and slice enough peaches to have 1-inch deep on the bottom of a greased 8-inch square pan.
Stir together flour, sugar, salt and cinnamon.
Cut butter into dry ingredients until mixture is crumbly.
Sprinkle on top of peaches.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: fidget pie(main dish)
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Butter a deep, 2-quart casserole.
Layer potato slices in the bottom of the casserole.
Season with salt, pepper, sage and nutmeg.
Continue layering and seasoning - first ham, then onion, finally apples.
Pour broth over all.
Roll out pastry on floured board until 1/4-inch thick.
Fit pastry over pie, sealing and fluting it to the edge of the casserole.
Cut a decorative hole in the center with a small cookie cutter so steam can escape.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350° and bake for 40 to 45 minutes until pastry is crisp and golden and potatoes are tender.

title: cran-apple jello salad
directions: Boil water; in bowl dissolve jello.
Add cranberry sauce and mix well.
Add applesauce and mix.
Put in refrigerator for 1 hour. This is good and fast when you need something to take out.

title: hello dollies
directions: Melt butter in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle crumbs over butter. Pour milk evenly over crumbs.
Top with remaining ingredients. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool before cutting.

title: swiss chocolate cake
directions: Mix together. Bake in 3 pans that have been greased and floured at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix together and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: soft pretzels
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Dissolve yeast in warm water; add sugar and salt.
Blend in flour.
Knead until smooth.
Cut into 10 to 12 pieces, roll into ropes and twist into desired shapes.
Place on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Brush with beaten egg and sprinkle with coarse salt.
Bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: In a medium saucepan, melt margarine.
Slowly stir in flour and milk.
Stir until thickened.
Add mayonnaise, lemon juice, curry powder and soup to saucepan.
Mix well.
Add pieces of chicken, stirring again.

title: baked fish with sour cream
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease an 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
In small bowl, combine sour cream, bread crumbs, mayonnaise, lemon juice, Tabasco and onion.
Pat fish steaks dry with paper towels. Place in baking dish.
Bake 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake 5 to 10 minutes longer or until fish flakes when tested with a fork.

title: potato salad
directions: In an 8-inch skillet sprayed with vegetable oil spray, cook egg product, covered, over very low heat just until set.
Cool and dice.

title: rice-a-roni salad
directions: Prepare Rice-A-Roni as directed on box. Cool.
Once rice is cool, mix all ingredients together.

title: delicious! chicken wraps
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Wrap each chicken breast half with 3 slices of dried beef.
Spread 1 can cream of mushroom soup on bottom of casserole dish.
Arrange chicken with dried beef in dish.
Add extra mushrooms and 2 slices American cheese over chicken if desired.
Spread second can of soup over top and cover. Bake for approximately 1 hour 15 minutes.

title: cooley's shrimp boil
directions: Bring water and all ingredients, except shrimp, to a rolling boil and boil for 8 to 10 minutes. Remove onion and add shrimp. Boil for 5 minutes and turn off heat. Let soak in pot for 10 to 25 minutes to reach the desired level of spice. Ice can be added for spicier cold shrimp.

title: mincemeat pie filling
directions: Boil meat and run through a grinder with suet.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Add meat stocks if more moisture is needed.

title: sweet and sour chops
directions: Brown chops in fat.
Add sauerkraut and brown sugar.
Cover with foil and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: chicken and sausage jambalaya
directions: Boil and debone fryer.
Saute onions, bell pepper and celery in oleo.
Add sausage and fry.
Add all other ingredients.
Place in heavy pot with lid.
Bring to boil; turn to low heat and simmer for 1 hour.

title: bean casserole
directions: Brown onions and bacon and drain.
Mix together and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown beef in small amount of oil.
Saute onion and garlic until soft, but not brown; add to beef.
Simmer for several minutes.
Season with salt, chili powder and cumin.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Dice up cauliflower and broccoli and put in bowl.
Add dressing and Bac*Os, then mix.
Put in the refrigerator until it is chilled.

title: blueberry something
directions: Mix oleo, flour and nuts together.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Beat powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Add Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled crust.
Now, put on filling and chill before serving.

title: eggplant fries
directions: Peel eggplants.
Cut in 1/2-inch strips.
Mix egg, milk, black pepper, salt and 1 cup flour; beat well.
Dip eggplants in batter. Put 4 cups flour in a shallow pan and roll eggplants.
Fry in deep fat at 350° until brown.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Stir in lemonade. Add cold water and cranberry juice. Place in large bowl with ice cubes or in molded ring. Pour in ginger ale just before serving. Add balls of sherbet if desired.

title: taste-like-a-brownie cookie
directions: Melt chocolate and set aside to cool.
Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and beat well after each addition.
Add chocolate and vanilla to mixture; mix well.
Combine with flour and cinnamon.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk (begin and end with flour).
Add nuts.
Cover and chill 2 hours.
Coat hands with powdered sugar.
Shape dough in balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Chill again for about 30 minutes.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: tabouli
directions: Combine bulgur, boiling water and salt.
Cover and let set 20 minutes.
Add lemon juice, garlic, oil and mint.
Mix and refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Just before serving , add vegetables and mix gently.

title: christmas punch
directions: Blend the cranberry juice, sugar, fruit juices, and almond extract.
Refrigerate, covered until serving time.
Just before serving, stir in ginger ale and sherbet.

title: chicken or turkey dressing
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine corn bread, bread cubes, salt and pepper and sage in a large bowl.
Saute onions and celery lightly in butter.
Add to corn bread mixture.
Add eggs and stock. Toss lightly.
Bake about 45 minutes.

title: sweet and sour cucumbers
directions: Combine sugar, vinegar, salt and pepper in a small saucepan. Heat until sugar is dissolved, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Pour over cucumbers.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut round steak into thin strips and saute in small amount of consomme.
Slowly add sour cream and flour alternately into rest of consomme.
When all is blended into a sauce, add onion and catsup and simmer with beef.
Bring noodles to a boil in large saucepan and cook until tender.
Drain and serve with stroganoff.

title: chocolate delight
directions: First Layer:
Mix together the flour, oleo and chopped nuts. Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: creole fish chowder
directions: In saucepot, saute onion, celery, green pepper and garlic in oil until crispy-tender.
Stir in rest of ingredients, except fish.
Cook 20 minutes, until tender.
Add fish and cook 12 minutes longer.
Serves 4.

title: overnight chicken
directions: Cook Creamettes according to directions; mix all ingredients together and place in 2-quart casserole and refrigerate overnight. Before placing in oven, top with buttered bread crumbs; bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: watergate salad
directions: Peel and slice oranges wagon wheel style.
Fix a layer of oranges; sprinkle with sugar and coconut.
Repeat this to how many layers you want.
Pick nice round oranges.
Use a square bowl 1-inch deep.
Goes very good with turkey and dressing.

title: turketti
directions: Cook spaghetti as package directs; drain.
Place turkey, pimento, green pepper and onion in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Pour in mushroom soup and turkey broth. Add salt, pepper, 1 1/4 cups grated cheese and spaghetti.
With 2 forks, lightly toss until all is well mixed and coated with sauce.
Sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup grated cheese on top of turkey mixture. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: saucy meat loaf
directions: In bowl, mix thoroughly 1 cup of gravy and remaining ingredients.
In 12 x 8-inch baking pan, firmly shape meat mixture into 8 x 4-inch loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Spoon off fat, reserving 1 tablespoon of drippings.

title: party potatoes
directions: Cook, drain and mash potatoes.
Add cream cheese, sour cream, all seasonings and butter; beat until light and fluffy, adding more sour cream if necessary for consistency.
Put in pretty casserole; pour over a little melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
May be refrigerated for several days.
Adjust heating time if cold when putting in oven.

title: chicken roll
directions: Press crescent rolls gently to flatten.
Mix chicken, mushrooms, cream cheese, water chestnuts, lemon pepper and 2 tablespoons soft butter.
Put approximately 1/4 cup mixture in each roll.
Fold to completely cover mixture.
Dip rolls in 3 tablespoons melted butter; roll in seasoned dressing mix (crushed fine), then in chopped nuts.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes in a 375° oven until lightly brown.
Serve topped with mixture of mushroom soup and sour cream.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: quick beer rolls
directions: Mix Bisquick and sugar.
Add 1/2 can beer at room temperature (must be warm so yeast will work).
Do not mix until smooth, just until beer is mixed in.
Drop by spoon into greased muffin tin. Dot top with butter.
Preheat oven and bake at 500° for 12 minutes. Yields 12 rolls.

title: okra and sausage jambalaya
directions: In large pan or skillet, add all ingredients and cook about an hour or until done.
Serve over hot rice.

title: pineapple-coconut cake
directions: Beat together well the cake mix, eggs and crushed pineapple. Pour into greased 9 x 13 glass baking dish. Sprinkle brown sugar and pecans on top. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
While cake is baking, prepare frosting.

title: zucchini nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: Combine until crumbly. Press into greased 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: broccoli rice au gratin
directions: Mix soup and Cheez Whiz; add cooked rice and cooked broccoli. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chicken fajita pizza
directions: Cut chicken into strips.
Saute chicken in large skillet that is coated with Pam over medium heat until done.
Stir in seasonings; add onion and green pepper.
Cook until veggies are practically done.
Spray pizza pan with Pam.
Unroll dough and place in pan.
Spread dough to cover pan.
Bake at 425°
for 6 to 8 minutes or until light brown.
Remove crust from oven.
Spread chicken mixture over crust.
Spoon picante over chicken and sprinkle with cheese.
Return to oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa together, then add the hot water. Cook on top of stove until thick.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Soften butter.
Mix with 1 egg and cake mix until crumbly. Add nuts, coconut or chips at this time, if desired.
Press in bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan.
Soften cream cheese and mix with sugar and 2 eggs.
Pour over cake mix.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: extra easy lasagna
directions: In 10-inch skillet over medium high heat, cook beef until brown, stirring to separate meat.
Drain fat.
Add pasta sauce; heat thoroughly, stirring occasionally.
In 2-quart oblong baking dish, spread 1 1/2 cups meat mixture.
Top with three uncooked lasagna noodles, half of the Ricotta cheese and half of the Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers.
Top with remaining meat mixture.
Slowly pour water around inside edge of baking dish. Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Uncover; bake 10 minutes more.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving. Garnish each serving with salad greens and tomatoes if desired.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: In saucepan, combine chicken, sour cream and chicken soup. Mix well.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until mixture is thoroughly heated.

title: better than store bought granola
directions: Combine the oats, coconut and seeds and bake in 300° oven for 20 minutes.
Simmer the margarine, sugar, honey and salt over low heat.
Remove from heat and add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
You may stir in 1/2 cup toasted wheat germ or oat bran.
Pour the mixture over the toasted oat mixture.
Mix well to coat evenly.
Raise heat to 350°.
Return to oven 5 minutes more.
Add 1/2 cup raisins.
Stir and press down.
Bake 5 more minutes or until golden.
Remove from oven and cool.
Break into large pieces and store in airtight container.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar. Bring to a boil the cocoa, oleo, oil and water.
Pour cocoa mixture over flour and sugar and mix well by hand. Add buttermilk, vanilla and eggs. Pour mixture in pan, greased and dusted with flour. Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: awesome strawberry cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box. Cool slightly. Pierce cake all over with a toothpick. Bring the strawberry soda and jello to a boil. Pour over cake. Spread strawberries on top of cake. Beat pudding with milk until slightly thick. Fold in Cool Whip by hand and ice the cake. Keep in refrigerator.

title: oyster crackers snack
directions: Mix together.
Put into 13 x 9-inch pan and bake for 30 minutes at 250°.
Stir at 15 minutes, between baking.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Let pie shells thaw. Boil chicken until done and tear into bite-size pieces.
Mix soup, broth, vegetables, chicken, salt, and pepper. Pour into deep dish pie crust.
Top with regular pie crust and pinch edges to seal.
Cut 4 slits in crust and bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: cheesecake snacks
directions: Beat cream cheese, vanilla and sugar until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread on graham crackers and top with fresh fruit, if desired.

title: brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Melt butter in microwave; stir in sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add cocoa; beat until well blended.
Add flour, baking powder and salt; beat well.
Stir in nuts.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until brownies just begin to pull away from sides of pan. Cool.
Cut into bars and eat.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Cook ground beef and onion until tender; drain.
Add salt, powder, pepper and mushrooms.
Cook for 3 minutes.
Stir in soup; simmer for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in sour cream and cook until heated.
Serve over noodles.

title: paul's stuffed peppers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut thin slice from stem end of each pepper; remove all seeds and membranes.
Wash peppers.
Cook peppers in boiling water 5 minutes; drain.

title: lemon jello cake
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Add cake mix.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° in prepared 9 x 13-inch pan.
While cake is still hot, with a large fork punch top of cake many times.
Pour the topping mixture over the cake, filling the holes.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on box; add oleo and 2/3 cup evaporated milk.
Pour 1/2 of batter in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: pineapple souffle
directions: Beat the eggs and 1/4 cup sugar in a 1-quart casserole.
Mix the pineapple and flour; add to the egg mixture, stirring slightly.
Melt the butter in a saucepan.
Add the bread cubes. When the bread has absorbed all of the butter, place on top of the casserole.
Lightly sprinkle with 1/4 cup sugar and the cinnamon mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all together.
Serve with fresh vegetables, cauliflower, carrots, broccoli.
May be used as chip dip.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Put cucumber mixture in a big pan and pour mix over it.
Heat jars, fill and seal upside-down.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and Cheddar cheese, mixing until well blended.
Add pimento, green pepper, onion, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice and seasonings.
Mix well.
Chill.
Shape into a ball.
Roll in chopped nuts, dried ham or bacon bits.

title: beer rolls
directions: Spray muffin pans.
Drop in batter and bake at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: dip for veggies
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve with chilled veggies.

title: zesty sub
directions: Cut bread in half.
Spread half with butter.
Stir together vinegar, oil and garlic salt.
Dip lettuce leaves into mixture. Season with salt and pepper.
Layer remaining ingredients on tomato slices.
Place top half of bread on filling.
Secure with toothpicks.
Makes 6 servings.

title: three bean salad
directions: Mix beans, green pepper and onion in a large bowl, and toss lightly. Put sugar, oil, vinegar, salt and pepper in saucepan and heat to dissolve sugar. Pour over vegetables. Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: jamaican coconut pie
directions: Sprinkle coconut in pie shell.
Cream butter; gradually beat in sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Pour over coconut in pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until slightly puffed on top.
Cool to room temperature.

title: jean's chicken
directions: Cut cooked chicken into strips.
Mix sour cream and soup.
Add both cheeses.
Spoon mixture into enchiladas.
Roll over and put in baking dish.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 325°.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: garden pasta bake
directions: Cook pasta as directed on package; drain. Cook onions in butter in 10-inch skillet until tender. Add tomatoes, corn, green beans and 1/2 of cheese. Stir in soup; mix well. Combine pasta with vegetable mixture. Season to taste with salt and pepper. Pour into 11 x 8-inch baking dish or casserole dish. Top with remaining cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until hot.

title: vanilla ice cream mixture
directions: Beat eggs until lemon colored.
Add sugar gradually and continue beating.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Place mixture into ice cream churn.
Place in ice cream freezer and ice and salt mixture.
Freeze.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Grate zucchini and mix with eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla. Sift together all dry ingredients.
Add to zucchini mixture.
Stir just until moistened.
Fold in nuts.
Pour batter into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: buttermilk coconut pie
directions: Mix butter, sugar and flour and then add remaining ingredients, except coconut. Mix well; pour into unbaked pie shell. Sprinkle with coconut (frozen and thawed). Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients well.
Pour into greased 2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.
Sprinkle with parsley flakes and paprika if desired.
Serves 8-12 people.

title: gooey cereal crunch balls
directions: Place first 4 ingredients in 4-quart microwave-safe mixing bowl.
Microwave on High (100%), uncovered, 2 to 2 1/2 minutes, until butter is melted and cream cheese is soft.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Shape into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Place on paper plates.
Let stand at room temperature until firm, about 1 hour.
Store in airtight container at room temperature.
Makes 36 balls.

title: dip for vegetables
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: company chicken
directions: Place cooking oil in pan and lightly brown chicken.
Add water, wine, broccoli and cream of chicken soup.
Bring to a full boil. Separate broccoli pieces as it cooks; stir in rice.
Cook; cover until chicken is tender and remove from heat.
Let stand for 5 minutes before serving.

title: lazy gal's delight
directions: Empty half of cake mix in ungreased 7 x 12-inch loaf pan. Spread filling over mix without stirring.
Sprinkle remaining mix over filling.
Pour water over all; drizzle butter over water. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.
Yield:
10 to 12 servings.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Measure and sift dry ingredients and set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, mix with beater at low speed the eggs, pumpkin and oil.
Slowly add the dry ingredients and beat at low speed until batter is well mixed.
Add nuts and raisins.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 4 x 8-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour on the middle rack.
Makes 3 to 4 loaves.

title: date bars
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder in a bowl; add dates and nuts and mix.
Beat eggs until very light.
Add sugar gradually and beat.
Add to flour and fruit mixture.
Spread thin in well oiled pans and bake in a 325° oven for about 40 minutes.
Remove from pan after it has been out of oven a few minutes and cut in strips.
Roll in powdered sugar and store in a tightly covered jar or box.

title: chocolate-coffee frosting
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients; blend until smooth.
Add confectioners sugar, stirring well.

title: dump cake
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan in a 350° oven.
Pour melted butter in a bowl. Set aside.
Layer undrained pineapple, apple pie filling, cherry pie filling and coconut in the same pan in the order listed.
Do not stir.
Sprinkle with cake mix.
Pour melted butter over top. Bake 30 minutes or until top begins to brown.
